sentences.name: 句子116
sentences.correct: Passage Two One of the biggest triggers for emotional eating is anger.
sentences.translate: 情绪化进食的最大诱因之一是愤怒。

sentences.name: 句子117
sentences.correct: Eating when we're angry, frustrated, irritated, feeling like we've been treated unfairly we may call it different names, but these words usually boil down to feeling angry.
sentences.translate: 当我们生气、沮丧、恼怒、感觉受到不公平对待时，我们可能会用不同的名字来称呼它，但这些词通常归结为愤怒。

sentences.name: 句子118
sentences.correct: Anger, makes many people especially womenuncomfortable.
sentences.translate: 愤怒，让许多人，尤其是女性感到不舒服。

sentences.name: 句子119
sentences.correct: Many of us go to great lengths to avoid expressing our anger directly.
sentences.translate: 我们中的许多人竭尽全力避免直接表达我们的愤怒。

sentences.name: 句子120
sentences.correct: Even when we've learned to face the conflicts and the sticky situations head-on in professional settings, we may still shy away from addressing our anger in our personal lives.
sentences.translate: 即使我们学会了在职业环境中直面冲突和棘手的情况，我们可能仍然会回避在个人生活中解决我们的愤怒。

sentences.name: 句子121
sentences.correct: Literally, many people swallow it.
sentences.translate: 从字面上看，很多人都吞下了它。

sentences.name: 句子122
sentences.correct: Many women who feel strong and competent in other areas of their lives, feel so uncomfortable with anger and frustration that they turn to food to avoid it, change it, bury it, or sometimes even turn the anger on themselves.
sentences.translate: 许多在生活的其他领域感到坚强和有能力的女性，对愤怒和沮丧感到非常不舒服，以至于她们转向食物来避免、改变、埋葬，有时甚至把愤怒发泄在自己身上。

sentences.name: 句子123
sentences.correct: Taking control of emotional eating isn't just about food.
sentences.translate: 控制情绪化饮食不仅仅是关于食物。

sentences.name: 句子124
sentences.correct: It's about taking on challenging issues and learning to cope with them differently and directly.
sentences.translate: 这是关于接受具有挑战性的问题，并学会以不同和直接的方式应对它们。

sentences.name: 句子125
sentences.correct: That's one of the reasons that taking charge of emotional eating is so empowering.
sentences.translate: 这就是负责情绪化饮食如此有力量的原因之一。

sentences.name: 句子126
sentences.correct: Taking charge of emotional eating transforms you.
sentences.translate: 控制情绪化饮食会改变你。

sentences.name: 句子127
sentences.correct: If we can't stand tall and face the conflicts head-on and if we don't have the tools to deal with anger in an effective manner that reflects our best selves, we're not fully in the game.
sentences.translate: 如果我们不能挺直腰板，直面冲突，如果我们没有有效地处理愤怒的工具来反映我们最好的自我，我们就没有完全参与游戏。

sentences.name: 句子128
sentences.correct: It's not about choosing different foods to eat; it's about learning the tools and strategies that help you move beyond emotional eating and dieting by approaching the rest of your life more effectively.
sentences.translate: 这不是关于选择不同的食物吃；这是关于学习工具和策略，通过更有效地度过余生，帮助你超越情绪化饮食和节食。

sentences.name: 句子129
sentences.correct: 陋陇Questions 20 to 22 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 陋陇根据你刚才听到的文章，回答20至22题。

sentences.translate: 22.我们应该做些什么来控制情绪化饮食？

sentences.name: 句子133
sentences.correct: Passage Three Charging your cell phone may soon require only two items: a simple piece of fabric and your body. Researchers have developed a Power Felt that uses thermoelectric technology to charge devices such as cell phones.
sentences.translate: 给手机充电可能很快只需要两件事：一块简单的布料和你的身体。研究人员开发了一种Power Felt，它使用热电技术为手机等设备充电。

sentences.name: 句子134
sentences.correct: Working in conjunction with outside temperatures, the material is capable of turning body heat into an electrical current to keep personal electronic devices up and running.
sentences.translate: 与外界温度协同工作，这种材料能够将身体热量转化为电流，以保持个人电子设备的正常运行。

sentences.name: 句子135
sentences.correct: Currently, the material only produces 140 nanowatts of power, which is about a millionth of the power your iPhone uses when it's idle, but scientists are doing further research and hoping to largely improve the quality of the material.
sentences.translate: 目前，这种材料只能产生140纳瓦的功率，大约是iPhone闲置时使用的功率的百万分之一，但科学家们正在进行进一步的研究，希望在很大程度上提高材料的质量。

sentences.name: 句子136
sentences.correct: Eventually, the research team hopes to market a phone-sized fabric swatch for just 1.
sentences.translate: 最终，研究小组希望以1美元的价格销售一款手机大小的布料样品。

sentences.name: 句子137
sentences.correct: It is said that charging a phone with the material is easy: just attach the fabric near the battery and hold the device in your hand.
sentences.translate: 据说用这种材料给手机充电很容易：只需将织物贴在电池附近，然后将设备拿在手里。

sentences.name: 句子138
sentences.correct: With further improvements, the device might come in handy for distance runners who need to charge their digital music players while they're out on the town.
sentences.translate: 随着进一步的改进，该设备可能会对需要在外出时为数字音乐播放器充电的长跑运动员派上用场。

sentences.name: 句子139
sentences.correct: It's pretty cool to make a jacket with a completely thermoelectric inside liner that gathers warmth from body heat, while the exterior remains cold from the outside temperature, and it's definitely within reach.
sentences.translate: 制作一件完全热电内衬的夹克非常酷，内衬可以从身体热量中收集热量，而外部则可以从外部温度中保持寒冷，而且绝对触手可及。

sentences.name: 句子140
sentences.correct: In addition to the obvious convenience factor, scientists said the material might be useful in urgent situations.
sentences.translate: 除了明显的便利因素外，科学家们表示，这种材料在紧急情况下可能有用。

sentences.name: 句子141
sentences.correct: You could imagine it in an emergency kit, wrapped around a flashlight, powering a weather radio...
sentences.translate: 你可以想象它放在一个应急包里，包在手电筒周围，为气象电台供电。。。

sentences.correct: News Report One There has been a shock in France at the revelation that the country's Culture Minister hasn't read a single novel in the past two years.

sentences.name: 句子8
sentences.correct: Our correspondent Lucy Williamson was reporting from Paris.

sentences.name: 句子9
sentences.correct: In the interview yesterday, Mrs. Pellerin described having had a wonderful lunch with the writer in question, Patrick Modiano, but wasn't able to say which of his titles she preferred because she said she hadn't had time to read his books or indeed any others since taking up a ministerial post two years ago.

sentences.name: 第 300 题 18

sentences.correct: News Report Three Not enough American students want to be engineers, mathematicians or scientists.
sentences.translate: 没有足够的美国学生想成为工程师、数学家或科学家。

sentences.correct: The government will invest three billion dollars in the education of young Americans in science, technology, engineering and math.

sentences.name: 句子24

sentences.translate: 这四个领域统称为STEM。

sentences.name: 句子26
sentences.correct: The US government's investment aims to increase the number of Americans who can take those jobs.
sentences.translate: 美国政府的投资旨在增加能够从事这些工作的美国人的数量。

sentences.name: 句子27
sentences.correct: Yet girls appear far less interested in STEM subjects than boys.
sentences.translate: 然而，女孩似乎对STEM科目的兴趣远低于男孩。

sentences.name: 句子31
sentences.correct: At school, girls should participate in projects that require teamwork and creative thinking.
sentences.translate: 在学校，女孩应该参与需要团队合作和创造性思维的项目。

sentences.name: 句子32
sentences.correct: Women in scientific and technical jobs are also working to encourage young women to explore STEM.
sentences.translate: 从事科技工作的女性也在努力鼓励年轻女性探索STEM。

sentences.name: 句子33

sentences.name: 句子46
sentences.correct: Conversation One M: Clifton Police Office.
sentences.translate: 对话一M：克利夫顿警察局。

sentences.name: 句子47
sentences.correct: Can I help you?
sentences.translate: 我能帮助你吗？

sentences.name: 句子48
sentences.correct: W: Yes. It's about my daughter, Mary.
sentences.translate: W： 是的。是关于我女儿玛丽的。

sentences.name: 句子49
sentences.correct: She went to school this morning but she hasn't arrived yet.
sentences.translate: 她今天早上去上学了，但还没到。

sentences.name: 句子50
sentences.correct: It's 11 o'clock.
sentences.translate: 现在是11点钟。

sentences.name: 句子51
sentences.correct: M: Just a moment, Mrs....?
sentences.translate: M： 等一下，夫人。。。。？

sentences.name: 句子52
sentences.correct: W: Mrs. Joe Smith, 43 Bath Road.
sentences.translate: W： 乔·史密斯太太，巴斯路43号。

sentences.name: 句子53
sentences.correct: M: Thank you. Now Mrs. Smith, what exactly is the matter?
sentences.translate: M： 谢谢。史密斯太太，到底怎么了？

sentences.name: 句子54
sentences.correct: W: Well, Mary left home this morning at about 9:00, and then her teacher telephoned me about an hour ago and asked if Mary was ill. I said no, and then she said she didn't see Mary this morning.
sentences.translate: W： 嗯，玛丽今天早上9点左右离开了家，然后她的老师大约一个小时前打电话给我，问玛丽是否病了。我说没有，然后她说她今天早上没见到玛丽。

sentences.name: 句子55
sentences.correct: M: I see. Now, let's have a few details.
sentences.translate: M： 我明白了。现在，让我们来了解一些细节。

sentences.name: 句子56
sentences.correct: How old is Mary?
sentences.translate: 玛丽多大了？

sentences.name: 句子57
sentences.correct: W: She is seven.
sentences.translate: W： 她七岁了。

sentences.name: 句子58
sentences.correct: M: And what does she look like?
sentences.translate: M： 她长什么样？

sentences.name: 句子59
sentences.correct: W: Well, she is slim and has long dark hair tied in a ponytail with a ribbon in it.
sentences.translate: W： 嗯，她很苗条，有一头长长的黑发，扎成马尾辫，上面系着缎带。

sentences.name: 句子60
sentences.correct: M: Yes, slim, long dark hair tied in a ponytail with a ribbon in it.
sentences.translate: M： 是的，又细又长的黑发扎成马尾，里面系着缎带。

sentences.name: 句子61
sentences.correct: And what color is the ribbon?
sentences.translate: 丝带是什么颜色的？

sentences.name: 句子62
sentences.correct: W: It's pink.
sentences.translate: W： 它是粉红色的。

sentences.name: 句子63
sentences.correct: M: Pink, OK. What does she wear?
sentences.translate: M： 粉红色，好的。她穿什么？

sentences.name: 句子64
sentences.correct: W: She is wearing a white short-sleeved blouse and a pink and white striped skirt, long stockings and black shoes.
sentences.translate: W： 她穿着白色短袖上衣、粉白色条纹裙、长袜和黑色鞋子。

sentences.name: 句子65
sentences.correct: M: Just a minute, let me write them down.
sentences.translate: M： 请稍等，让我把它们写下来。

sentences.name: 句子66
sentences.correct: A white short-sleeved blouse and a pink and white striped skirt, with long stockings and black shoes.
sentences.translate: 一件白色短袖上衣和一条粉白色条纹裙，搭配长袜和黑色鞋子。

sentences.name: 句子67
sentences.correct: Is that right?
sentences.translate: 是吗？

sentences.name: 句子68
sentences.correct: W: Yes, exactly.
sentences.translate: W： 没错。

sentences.name: 句子69
sentences.correct: M: All right, Mrs. Smith, we will help you find your daughter.
sentences.translate: M： 好的，史密斯太太，我们会帮你找到你的女儿。

sentences.name: 句子70
sentences.correct: We'll give you a call as soon as we get the information about your daughter.
sentences.translate: 我们一得到你女儿的消息就会给你打电话。

sentences.name: 句子78
sentences.correct: How was the West Coast?

sentences.name: 句子79
sentences.correct: W: Terrific. It was really nice to get away from the city for a while.
sentences.translate: W： 太棒了。离开城市一段时间真的很好。

sentences.name: 句子80
sentences.correct: M: What did you think of L.A.?
sentences.translate: M： 你觉得洛杉矶怎么样。？

sentences.name: 句子81
sentences.correct: W: It's very clean and spacious, and it's got lots of trees.
sentences.translate: W： 它非常干净宽敞，而且有很多树。

sentences.name: 句子82
sentences.correct: The problem is transportation.
sentences.translate: 问题是交通。

sentences.name: 句子83
sentences.correct: The bus service is terrible and there is no subway, so it's a little difficult to get around.
sentences.translate: 公共汽车服务很糟糕，而且没有地铁，所以出行有点困难。

sentences.name: 句子84
sentences.correct: M: And what did you see?
sentences.translate: M： 你看到了什么？

sentences.name: 句子85
sentences.correct: W: We took a drive around Hollywood and looked at the stars' homes and then we went to Universal Studios and Disneyland.
sentences.translate: W： 我们开车在好莱坞转转，看看明星们的家，然后去了环球影城和迪士尼乐园。

sentences.name: 句子86
sentences.correct: M: How did you like Disneyland?
sentences.translate: M： 你觉得迪士尼乐园怎么样？

sentences.name: 句子87
sentences.correct: W: Great! We really enjoyed it.
sentences.translate: W： 太棒了！我们真的很享受。

sentences.name: 句子88
sentences.correct: We took all the rides, some of them twice and had lots of fun.
sentences.translate: 我们乘坐了所有的游乐设施，其中一些是两次，玩得很开心。

sentences.name: 句子89
sentences.correct: I felt just like a kid again.
sentences.translate: 我感觉自己又像个孩子了。

sentences.name: 句子90
sentences.correct: M: Was the weather good?
sentences.translate: M： 天气好吗？

sentences.name: 句子91
sentences.correct: W: It was nice and warm in L.A., and cool but comfortable in San Francisco.
sentences.translate: W： 洛杉矶的天气很好很温暖，旧金山的天气很凉爽但很舒适。

sentences.name: 句子92
sentences.correct: M: Cool in San Francisco? That's surprising.
sentences.translate: M： 旧金山很酷？这太令人惊讶了。

sentences.name: 句子93
sentences.correct: W: Yeah, it surprised us a bit, too.
sentences.translate: W： 是啊，这也让我们有点惊讶。

sentences.name: 句子94
sentences.correct: We didn't take any sweaters or anything.
sentences.translate: 我们没有带任何毛衣或任何东西。

sentences.name: 句子95
sentences.correct: But they say it's always like that in August.
sentences.translate: 但他们说八月总是这样。

sentences.name: 句子96

sentences.translate: 不管怎样，我只是喜欢它。

sentences.translate: 它可能是美国最美丽的城镇。

sentences.name: 句子98

sentences.name: 句子99
sentences.correct: W: Oh, yes. There's much more to see and do.
sentences.translate: W： 哦，是的。还有更多的东西要看和做。

sentences.name: 句子100

sentences.name: 句子101

sentences.correct: Passage One Welcome to Ealing College of Higher Education(ECHE).

sentences.name: 句子116

sentences.correct: on Fridays during term time.
sentences.translate: 在学期期间的星期五。

sentences.name: 句子126
sentences.correct: The college doctor, Dr. Kearns, holds a surgery in the medical center four days a week: Monday and Tuesday mornings, Thursday afternoons and either Wednesday or Friday afternoons.
sentences.translate: 大学医生卡恩斯博士每周四天在医疗中心进行手术：周一和周二上午、周四下午以及周三或周五下午。

sentences.name: 句子127
sentences.correct: Appointments for these surgeries are made through the nurses and are usually for the following day.
sentences.translate: 这些手术的预约是通过护士进行的，通常是在第二天。

sentences.name: 句子128
sentences.correct: Besides these times, Dr. Kearns can be found at her surgery which is located at No. 2 Ascott Avenue.
sentences.translate: 除了这些时间，Kearns医生还可以在她位于雅诗阁大道2号的手术室找到。

sentences.name: 句子129
sentences.correct: During your stay in England, you must register with a local doctor and if you live in the London Borough of Ealing, you can register with Dr. Kearns.
sentences.translate: 在英国逗留期间，您必须向当地医生登记，如果您住在伦敦伊林区，您可以向卡恩斯医生登记。

sentences.name: 句子130
sentences.correct: Questions 16 to 18 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答问题16至18。

sentences.name: 第 16 题 131
sentences.correct: 16. What does the speaker say about the Student Union?
sentences.translate: 16.演讲者对学生会说了什么？

sentences.name: 第 17 题 132
sentences.correct: 17. When is the student health center open?
sentences.translate: 17.学生健康中心什么时候开放？

sentences.name: 第 18 题 133
sentences.correct: 18. What do we learn about Dr. Kearns?
sentences.translate: 18.我们对卡恩斯博士了解多少？

sentences.name: 句子134
sentences.correct: Passage Two For every woman who feels like she's had to give up her personal ambitions since becoming a mother, gold medal cyclist Kristin Armstrong has a message: Don't give up on your dreams.
sentences.translate: 对于每一位自成为母亲以来就不得不放弃个人抱负的女性，金牌自行车手克里斯汀·阿姆斯特朗都有一个信息：不要放弃你的梦想。

sentences.name: 句子135
sentences.correct: She retired to start a family after winning a gold medal.
sentences.translate: 她在获得金牌后退休成家。

sentences.name: 句子136
sentences.correct: Her son Lucas arrived in 2010, but then she decided she wanted to compete again in the Olympics.
sentences.translate: 她的儿子卢卡斯于2010年出生，但后来她决定再次参加奥运会。

sentences.name: 句子137
sentences.correct: The decision to start training again wasn't easy.
sentences.translate: 重新开始训练的决定并不容易。

sentences.name: 句子138
sentences.correct: I struggled with that a lot, she told a newspaper.
sentences.translate: 她告诉一家报纸说：“我对此很纠结。”。

sentences.name: 句子139
sentences.correct: At the beginning I felt selfish.
sentences.translate: 一开始我觉得很自私。

sentences.name: 句子140
sentences.correct: I felt like, well, I'm not supposed to be thinking of myself anymore, and it's all supposed to be for my kid. She faced physical challenges of getting back into competition shape after giving birth as well.
sentences.translate: 我觉得，好吧，我不应该再为自己着想了，这一切都应该是为了我的孩子。她在分娩后也面临着恢复比赛状态的身体挑战。

sentences.name: 句子141
sentences.correct: When she started racing in the next year, she was still breast-feeding; she would nurse her son, then race, then breast-feed again after the race.
sentences.translate: 当她第二年开始参加比赛时，她还在哺乳；她会先给儿子喂奶，然后比赛，比赛结束后再母乳喂养。

sentences.name: 句子142
sentences.correct: Her days revolved around Lucas and training.
sentences.translate: 她的日子围绕着卢卡斯和训练。

sentences.name: 句子143
sentences.correct: I feel like I'm able to do what I love to do and still manage a family and have that balance, Armstrong said.
sentences.translate: 阿姆斯特朗说：“我觉得我能够做我喜欢做的事情，同时还能管理一个家庭，并保持这种平衡。”。

sentences.name: 句子144
sentences.correct: That you have a family or a child doesn't mean that you have to stop going after what you dream of. However, it doesn't look that easy.
sentences.translate: 你有一个家庭或孩子并不意味着你必须停止追求你的梦想。然而，这看起来并不容易。

sentences.name: 句子145
sentences.correct: She points out that we can't have it all without making some sacrifices.
sentences.translate: 她指出，如果不做出一些牺牲，我们就无法拥有一切。

sentences.name: 句子146
sentences.correct: For example, don't expect a neat home she's had to give up on trying to keep everything orderly at home and just accept that their living room has become Lucas's playroom.
sentences.translate: 例如，不要指望一个整洁的家——她不得不放弃努力让家里的一切井然有序，只接受他们的客厅已经成为卢卡斯的游戏室。

sentences.name: 句子147
sentences.correct: Moreover, she's sacrificed time with friends who had kids around the same age there just wasn't time.
sentences.translate: 此外，她牺牲了与有同龄孩子的朋友在一起的时间，只是没有时间。

sentences.name: 句子148
sentences.correct: Questions 19 to 21 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答19至21题。

sentences.name: 第 19 题 149
sentences.correct: 19. What can we learn about Kristin Armstrong after she retired?
sentences.translate: 19.克里斯汀·阿姆斯特朗退役后，我们能从她身上学到什么？

sentences.name: 第 20 题 150
sentences.correct: 20. Why did Kristin Armstrong struggle a lot to make the decision to start training again?
sentences.translate: 20.为什么Kristin Armstrong在决定再次开始训练时遇到了很多困难？

sentences.name: 第 21 题 151
sentences.correct: 21. What was Kristin Armstrong described as after she restarted racing?
sentences.translate: 21.Kristin Armstrong在重新开始比赛后被描述为什么？

sentences.name: 句子152
sentences.correct: Passage Three Every second in the US alone, more than 250 animals are slaughtered for food, adding up to more than eight billion animals each year.
sentences.translate: 仅在美国，每秒就有250多只动物被屠宰作为食物，每年加起来超过80亿只动物。

sentences.name: 句子153
sentences.correct: Reducing the amount of meat in one's diet is nutritionally, environmentally and ethically beneficial.
sentences.translate: 减少饮食中的肉类摄入在营养、环境和道德上都是有益的。

sentences.name: 句子154
sentences.correct: People who eat meat usually have weaker immune systems compared to those vegetarians.
sentences.translate: 与素食者相比，吃肉的人通常免疫系统较弱。

sentences.name: 句子155
sentences.correct: Furthermore, meat-eaters are at a higher risk for diseases including cancer, and they are more likely to die from these diseases.
sentences.translate: 此外，肉类食者患包括癌症在内的疾病的风险更高，他们更有可能死于这些疾病。

sentences.name: 句子156
sentences.correct: Critics say that a meatless diet does not provide enough nutrients, especially protein and iron.
sentences.translate: 批评者说，无肉饮食不能提供足够的营养，尤其是蛋白质和铁。

sentences.name: 句子157
sentences.correct: Actually, protein is found in almost every food, and iron appears in many vegetables.
sentences.translate: 事实上，蛋白质几乎存在于每种食物中，铁存在于许多蔬菜中。

sentences.name: 句子158
sentences.correct: Getting enough nutrients in a meat-reduced diet should not be difficult.
sentences.translate: 在减少肉类的饮食中获得足够的营养应该不难。

sentences.name: 句子159
sentences.correct: Diet including more fruits and vegetables will only make people healthier.
sentences.translate: 多吃水果和蔬菜只会让人更健康。

sentences.name: 句子160
sentences.correct: Some skeptics believe that there will be a shortage of food if animals are not eaten.
sentences.translate: 一些怀疑论者认为，如果不吃动物，就会出现食物短缺。

sentences.name: 句子161
sentences.correct: In fact, the opposite is true.
sentences.translate: 事实上，情况恰恰相反。

sentences.name: 句子162
sentences.correct: More than 80% of the corn and 95% of the oats grown in the US are fed to livestock.
sentences.translate: 美国种植的80%以上的玉米和95%的燕麦都是用来喂牲畜的。

sentences.name: 句子163
sentences.correct: The world's cattle alone consume enough food to equal the calorie needs of 8.7 billion people, more than the entire human population.
sentences.translate: 仅世界上的牛就消耗了足够的食物，相当于87亿人的卡路里需求，超过了整个人口。

sentences.name: 句子164
sentences.correct: One half of the water used in the US also goes to livestock.
sentences.translate: 美国一半的用水也用于牲畜。

sentences.name: 句子165
sentences.correct: If people eat less meat and more plants, the amount of available food will increase.
sentences.translate: 如果人们少吃肉，多吃植物，可用的食物量就会增加。

sentences.name: 句子166
sentences.correct: Many people become vegetarians because they feel that eating animals is unethical.
sentences.translate: 许多人成为素食主义者是因为他们觉得吃动物是不道德的。

sentences.name: 句子167
sentences.correct: Ninety percent of these animals are raised in confinement.
sentences.translate: 这些动物中有90%是在禁闭中饲养的。

sentences.name: 句子168
sentences.correct: Chicken and other birds have only about half a square foot of space each, and since they are raised so close together, a hot blade is used to cut off their beaks to prevent them from pecking each other to death.
sentences.translate: 鸡和其他鸟类每只只有大约半平方英尺的空间，由于它们被饲养得如此之近，人们用一把热刀切掉它们的喙，以防止它们互相啄死。

sentences.name: 句子169
sentences.correct: Questions 22 to 25 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答问题22至25。

sentences.name: 第 22 题 170
sentences.correct: 22. What's the passage mainly about?
sentences.translate: 22.这篇文章主要讲什么？

sentences.name: 第 23 题 171
sentences.correct: 23. Which is one of the reasons why we should eat less meat?
sentences.translate: 23.我们应该少吃肉的原因之一是什么？

sentences.name: 第 24 题 172
sentences.correct: 24. Why does the speaker say eating less meat is environmentally beneficial?
sentences.translate: 24.为什么演讲者说少吃肉对环境有益？

sentences.name: 第 25 题 173
sentences.correct: 25. Why do many people become vegetarians according to the speaker?
sentences.translate: 25.根据演讲者的说法，为什么很多人成为素食主义者？

sentences.correct: This is the end of listening comprehension.
sentences.translate: 听力理解到此结束。

sentences.correct: Model Test 6 Section A Directions: In this section, you will hear three news reports.
sentences.translate: 模型测试6 A部分说明：在本节中，您将听到三篇新闻报道。

sentences.correct: At the end of each news report, you will hear two or three questions.
sentences.translate: 在每一篇新闻报道的结尾，你会听到两三个问题。

sentences.name: A 部分题干3
sentences.correct: Both the news report and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道和提问都只会说一次。

sentences.name: A 部分题干4
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。

sentences.name: A 部分题干结束5

sentences.translate: 然后在答题纸1上用一条穿过中心的线标记相应的字母。

sentences.name: 句子6
sentences.correct: News Report One New York State plans to shut off the thundering waters of Niagara Falls—again.
sentences.translate: 纽约州计划再次关闭尼亚加拉大瀑布的雷鸣般的水域。

sentences.name: 句子7
sentences.correct: At least, the American side of the falls.
sentences.translate: 至少，美国方面的下跌。

sentences.name: 句子8
sentences.correct: This “once in a lifetime”event actually may take place twice in some folks' lives.
sentences.translate: 这种“一生一次”的事件实际上可能会在一些人的生活中发生两次。

sentences.name: 句子9
sentences.correct: The New York State parks system wants to turn off the falls on the American side sometime in the next two to three years to replace two 115-year-old stone bridges that allow pedestrians, park vehicles and utilities access to Goat Island.
sentences.translate: 纽约州立公园系统希望在未来两三年内关闭美国一侧的瀑布，以取代两座有115年历史的石桥，这两座石桥允许行人、停车车辆和公用事业进入山羊岛。

sentences.name: 句子10
sentences.correct: The American side of the falls were shut off in 1969 to study the buildup of rock at the base of the falls.
sentences.translate: 1969年，瀑布的美国一侧被关闭，以研究瀑布底部的岩石堆积。

sentences.name: 句子11
sentences.correct: When that happened, people came from all over the world to see the falls turned off.
sentences.translate: 当这种情况发生时，人们从世界各地赶来观看瀑布的关闭。

sentences.name: 句子12
sentences.correct: People are curious by nature.
sentences.translate: 人们天生好奇。

sentences.name: 句子13
sentences.correct: They want to see what's underneath.
sentences.translate: 他们想看看下面是什么。

sentences.name: 句子14
sentences.correct: In fact, those who first came to have a look did see something.
sentences.translate: 事实上，那些第一个来看的人确实看到了一些东西。

sentences.name: 句子15
sentences.correct: They found millions of coins on the bottom.
sentences.translate: 他们在底部发现了数百万枚硬币。

sentences.name: 句子16
sentences.correct: Questions 1 and 2 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题1和2基于你刚才听到的新闻报道。

sentences.name: 第 1 题 17
sentences.correct: 1. Why does New York State want to turn off Niagara Falls?
sentences.translate: 1.纽约州为什么要关闭尼亚加拉大瀑布？

sentences.name: 第 2 题 18
sentences.correct: 2. What did people find when Niagara Falls were shut off in 1969?
sentences.translate: 2.1969年尼亚加拉大瀑布被关闭时，人们发现了什么？

sentences.name: 句子19
sentences.correct: News Report Two The Tunisian government said Monday that 45 people have been killed after gunmen attacked a town near the border with Libya.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道二突尼斯政府周一表示，枪手袭击了靠近利比亚边境的一个城镇，造成45人死亡。

sentences.name: 句子20
sentences.correct: The Interior and Defense ministries said that the Tunisian government has closed its two border crossings with Libya because of the attack.
sentences.translate: 内政部和国防部表示，由于袭击事件，突尼斯政府关闭了与利比亚的两个过境点。

sentences.name: 句子21
sentences.correct: The Tunisian military has sent reinforcements and helicopters to the area, and authorities have been hunting several attackers who were still at large.
sentences.translate: 突尼斯军方已向该地区派遣增援部队和直升机，当局一直在追捕几名仍在逃的袭击者。

sentences.name: 句子22
sentences.correct: The violence came amid increasing international concern about Islamic State extremists in Libya.
sentences.translate: 暴力事件发生之际，国际社会对利比亚伊斯兰国极端分子的担忧日益加剧。

sentences.name: 句子23
sentences.correct: Officials of the Tunisian government are especially worried after dozens of tourists were killed in the attacks in Tunisia last year.
sentences.translate: 去年突尼斯发生的袭击事件导致数十名游客死亡，突尼斯政府官员对此尤为担忧。

sentences.name: 句子24
sentences.correct: Defense Minister Farhat Horchani said last week the German and American security experts were expected to come to help Tunisia devise a new electronic video supervision system on its border with Libya.
sentences.translate: 国防部长Farhat Horchani上周表示，预计德国和美国安全专家将前来帮助突尼斯在与利比亚接壤的边境设计一个新的电子视频监控系统。

sentences.name: 句子25
sentences.correct: Tunisia was targeted last year by three attacks that left 70 people dead and were claimed by Islamic State.
sentences.translate: 突尼斯去年遭受了三次袭击，造成70人死亡，伊斯兰国声称对其负责。

sentences.name: 句子26
sentences.correct: Questions 3 and 4 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题3和4基于你刚才听到的新闻报道。

sentences.name: 第 3 题 27
sentences.correct: 3. What did the Tunisian government do after the gunmen's attack?
sentences.translate: 3.枪手袭击后突尼斯政府做了什么？

sentences.name: 第 4 题 28
sentences.correct: 4. What were German and American security experts expected to do in Tunisia?
sentences.translate: 4.德国和美国的安全专家预计在突尼斯做什么？

sentences.name: 句子29
sentences.correct: News Report Three Three university students in Santiago, Chile, have developed a plant-powered device to charge their mobile phones.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道三智利圣地亚哥的三名大学生开发了一种植物供电的手机充电设备。

sentences.name: 句子30
sentences.correct: The three engineering students got the idea for the device while sitting in their school's courtyard.
sentences.translate: 三名工科学生坐在学校的院子里时想到了这个装置。

sentences.name: 句子31
sentences.correct: Their invention is a small biological circuit they call E-Kaia.
sentences.translate: 他们的发明是一种他们称之为E-Kaia的小型生物回路。

sentences.name: 句子32
sentences.correct: It captures the energy which plants produce during photosynthesis— a process of converting sunlight into energy.
sentences.translate: 它捕获植物在光合作用过程中产生的能量，光合作用是将阳光转化为能量的过程。

sentences.name: 句子33
sentences.correct: A plant uses only a small part of the energy produced by that process.
sentences.translate: 植物只使用该过程产生的一小部分能量。

sentences.name: 句子34
sentences.correct: The rest goes into the soil.
sentences.translate: 其余的进入土壤。

sentences.name: 句子35
sentences.correct: E-Kaia collects that energy.
sentences.translate: E-Kaia收集这种能量。

sentences.name: 句子36
sentences.correct: The device plugs into the ground and then into a mobile phone.
sentences.translate: 该设备插入地面，然后插入手机。

sentences.name: 句子37
sentences.correct: The E-Kaia solves two problems for the engineering students.
sentences.translate: E-Kaia为工科学生解决了两个问题。

sentences.name: 句子38
sentences.correct: They needed an idea for a class project.
sentences.translate: 他们需要一个班级项目的想法。

sentences.name: 句子39
sentences.correct: They also needed an outlet to plug in their phones.
sentences.translate: 他们还需要一个插座来插入手机。

sentences.name: 句子40
sentences.correct: One of the student inventors, Camila Rupcich, says the device changes the energy released from the plant into low-level power to charge phones.
sentences.translate: 学生发明家之一Camila Rupcich表示，该设备将工厂释放的能量转化为低电平电力，为手机充电。

sentences.name: 句子41
sentences.correct: The E-Kaia is able to fully recharge a mobile phone in less than two hours.
sentences.translate: E-Kaia能够在不到两个小时的时间内为手机完全充电。

sentences.name: 句子42
sentences.correct: Questions 5 to 7 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的新闻报道，回答问题5至7。

sentences.name: 第 5 题 43
sentences.correct: 5. What did the three university students invent?
sentences.translate: 5.这三个大学生发明了什么？

sentences.name: 第 6 题 44
sentences.correct: 6. When did they get the idea for the invention?
sentences.translate: 6.他们什么时候想到这项发明的？

sentences.name: 第 7 题 45
sentences.correct: 7. What does the speaker say about the invention?
sentences.translate: 7.演讲者对这项发明说了什么？

sentences.name: B 部分题干46
sentences.correct: Section B Directions: In this section, you will hear two long conversations.
sentences.translate: B部分说明：在本节中，您将听到两段长对话。

sentences.name: B 部分题干47
sentences.correct: At the end of each conversation, you will hear four questions.
sentences.translate: 在每次对话结束时，您将听到四个问题。

sentences.name: B 部分题干48
sentences.correct: Both the conversation and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 对话和问题只会说一次。

sentences.name: B 部分题干49
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。

sentences.name: B 部分题干结束50
sentences.correct: Then mark the corresponding letter on Answer Sheet 1 with a single line through the centre.
sentences.translate: 然后在答题纸1上用一条穿过中心的线标记相应的字母。

sentences.name: 句子51
sentences.correct: Conversation One M: Good morning.
sentences.translate: M：早上好。

sentences.name: 句子52
sentences.correct: What can I do for you?
sentences.translate: 我能为你做什么？

sentences.name: 句子53
sentences.correct: W: Good morning.
sentences.translate: W： 早上好。

sentences.name: 句子54
sentences.correct: Could I talk to Jeffry Harding please?
sentences.translate: 我能和杰弗里·哈丁谈谈吗？

sentences.name: 句子55
sentences.correct: M: Speaking.
sentences.translate: M： 说话。

sentences.name: 句子56
sentences.correct: W: Hello, Jeff.
sentences.translate: W： 你好，杰夫。

sentences.name: 句子57
sentences.correct: It's Helen.
sentences.translate: 我是海伦。

sentences.name: 句子58
sentences.correct: I got your message on the answering machine.
sentences.translate: 我在答录机上收到了你的信息。

sentences.name: 句子59
sentences.correct: What's the problem?
sentences.translate: 有什么问题吗？

sentences.name: 句子60
sentences.correct: M: Oh, Helen.
sentences.translate: M： 哦，海伦。

sentences.name: 句子61
sentences.correct: Well, it's the Grimsby plant again, I'm afraid.
sentences.translate: 好吧，恐怕又是格里姆斯比工厂了。

sentences.name: 句子62
sentences.correct: The robots on Line 3 have gone wrong.
sentences.translate: 3号线上的机器人出了问题。

sentences.name: 句子63
sentences.correct: And the line is at a standstill.
sentences.translate: 生产线处于停滞状态。

sentences.name: 句子64
sentences.correct: W: Can't you replace them with the stand-ins?
sentences.translate: W： 你不能用替身代替他们吗？

sentences.name: 句子65
sentences.correct: M: I'm afraid not.
sentences.translate: M： 恐怕不行。

sentences.name: 句子66
sentences.correct: The stand-ins are already in use on Line 6.
sentences.translate: 这些替代品已经在6号线投入使用。

sentences.name: 句子67
sentences.correct: And the ones from Line 6 are being serviced.
sentences.translate: 6号线的列车正在维修中。

sentences.name: 句子68
sentences.correct: W: When did this happen, Jeff?
sentences.translate: W： 这是什么时候发生的，杰夫？

sentences.name: 句子69
sentences.correct: M: Well, they've been making a low continuous sound for a day or two.
sentences.translate: M： 嗯，他们已经连续发出低沉的声音一两天了。

sentences.name: 句子70
sentences.correct: But they finally went dead at 2:30 this afternoon.
sentences.translate: 但他们最终在今天下午2:30去世了。

sentences.name: 句子71
sentences.correct: W: I see.
sentences.translate: W： 我明白了。

sentences.name: 句子72
sentences.correct: What did you do?
sentences.translate: 你做了什么？

sentences.name: 句子73
sentences.correct: Have you tried the Hall plant?
sentences.translate: 你试过霍尔植物吗？

sentences.name: 句子74
sentences.correct: M: Not yet, Helen.
sentences.translate: M： 还没有，海伦。

sentences.name: 句子75
sentences.correct: I thought I'd better get your OK first.
sentences.translate: 我想我最好先征得你的同意。

sentences.name: 句子76
sentences.correct: W: OK.
sentences.translate: W： 好的。

sentences.name: 句子77
sentences.correct: Get on the phone to Tom, and try to get their stand-ins over tonight.
sentences.translate: 给汤姆打电话，试着让他们的替身今晚过去。

sentences.name: 句子78
sentences.correct: We have to be back at full capacity tomorrow morning.
sentences.translate: 我们明天早上必须满负荷返回。

sentences.name: 句子79
sentences.correct: Is it a major job to repair our robots?
sentences.translate: 修理我们的机器人是一项重要的工作吗？

sentences.name: 句子80
sentences.correct: M: About a week.
sentences.translate: M： 大约一周。

sentences.name: 句子81
sentences.correct: That's what the maintenance engineer says.
sentences.translate: 维修工程师就是这么说的。

sentences.name: 句子82
sentences.correct: W: Right.
sentences.translate: W： 对。

sentences.name: 句子83
sentences.correct: Well, if you can get the ones from Hall, please ask Tom to inform Sheffield that he may need their stand-ins in case of emergency during the next week.
sentences.translate: 好吧，如果你能从霍尔那里得到这些，请让汤姆通知谢菲尔德，他可能需要他们的替身，以防下周发生紧急情况。

sentences.name: 句子84
sentences.correct: M: OK.
sentences.translate: M： 好的。

sentences.name: 句子85
sentences.correct: Thank you very much, Helen.
sentences.translate: 非常感谢，海伦。

sentences.name: 句子86
sentences.correct: W: You are most welcome.
sentences.translate: W： 欢迎光临。

sentences.name: 句子87
sentences.correct: M: Sorry to spoil your day off.
sentences.translate: M： 很抱歉打扰了你的休息日。

sentences.name: 句子88
sentences.correct: W: It doesn't matter.
sentences.translate: W： 没关系。

sentences.name: 句子89
sentences.correct: Questions 8 to 11 are based on the conversation you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题8至11基于你刚才听到的对话。

sentences.name: 第 8 题 90
sentences.correct: 8. What did the man do before the telephone conversation?
sentences.translate: 8.在电话交谈之前，这个人做了什么？

sentences.name: 第 9 题 91
sentences.correct: 9. What does the man say about Line 3 in the Grimsby plant?
sentences.translate: 9.那人对格里姆斯比工厂的3号线怎么说？

sentences.name: 第 10 题 92
sentences.correct: 10. What is the man's purpose in calling the woman?
sentences.translate: 10.男人打电话给女人的目的是什么？

sentences.name: 第 11 题 93
sentences.correct: 11. Where is the woman at the time of the conversation?
sentences.translate: 11.谈话时女人在哪里？

sentences.name: 句子94
sentences.correct: Conversation Two W: This is Kerry Burke from New York Daily News.
sentences.translate: 对话二W：我是《纽约每日新闻》的Kerry Burke。

sentences.name: 句子95
sentences.correct: I'm speaking to Delroy Simmonds, an unemployed Brooklyn man who missed a job interview Tuesday for the best of reasons: He was saving the life of a 9-month-old boy who was blown into the path of an oncoming subway train by a high wind.
sentences.translate: 我正在与Delroy Simmonds交谈，他是一名失业的布鲁克林男子，周二错过了一次工作面试，原因有很多：他正在救一名9个月大的男孩的命，这名男孩被大风吹到了迎面而来的地铁列车上。

sentences.name: 句子96
sentences.correct: M: Everybody is making me out to be some sort of superhero.
sentences.translate: M： 每个人都把我描绘成某种超级英雄。

sentences.name: 句子97
sentences.correct: I'm just an ordinary person, and a father of two.
sentences.translate: 我只是一个普通人，也是两个孩子的父亲。

sentences.name: 句子98
sentences.correct: Anybody in that situation would have done what I did.
sentences.translate: 在那种情况下，任何人都会做我做的事。

sentences.name: 句子99
sentences.correct: W: You were going to an interview when the incident occurred, right?
sentences.translate: W： 事件发生时，你正准备去面试，对吗？

sentences.name: 句子100
sentences.correct: M: Yes, I was on my way to apply for a maintenance position.
sentences.translate: M： 是的，我正要去申请维修工作。

sentences.name: 句子101
sentences.correct: I've been looking for a job for a year and more.
sentences.translate: 我找工作已经一年多了。

sentences.name: 句子102
sentences.correct: I'm looking for something to support my family.
sentences.translate: 我在找东西养家糊口。

sentences.name: 句子103
sentences.correct: W: Tell us what happened at the station.
sentences.translate: W： 告诉我们车站发生了什么事。

sentences.name: 句子104
sentences.correct: M: There was a strong wind.
sentences.translate: M： 风很大。

sentences.name: 句子105
sentences.correct: It had to be 30 to 40 miles an hour.
sentences.translate: 它必须是每小时30到40英里。

sentences.name: 句子106
sentences.correct: There was a woman with four kids.
sentences.translate: 有一个女人有四个孩子。

sentences.name: 句子107
sentences.correct: One was in a pushchair.
sentences.translate: 一个坐在婴儿车里。

sentences.name: 句子108
sentences.correct: The wind blew the baby onto the tracks.
sentences.translate: 风把婴儿吹到了铁轨上。

sentences.name: 句子109
sentences.correct: W: Witnesses said people were looking on in horror as the child's mother, identified by sources as Maria Zamara, stood frozen in shock.
sentences.translate: W： 目击者说，人们惊恐地看着孩子的母亲，据消息人士称，她叫玛丽亚·扎马拉，站在那里惊呆了。

sentences.name: 句子110
sentences.correct: In the distance, people could see the train rounding a bend, headed into the station.
sentences.translate: 在远处，人们可以看到火车绕过弯道，驶向车站。

sentences.name: 句子111
sentences.correct: I guess you were not aware of any of these, right?
sentences.translate: 我想你不知道这些，对吧？

sentences.name: 句子112
sentences.correct: M: No.
sentences.translate: M： 没有。

sentences.name: 句子113
sentences.correct: I just jumped down and grabbed the baby.
sentences.translate: 我跳下来抓住了婴儿。

sentences.name: 句子114
sentences.correct: The train was coming around the corner as I lifted the baby from the tracks.
sentences.translate: 当我把婴儿从铁轨上抱起来时，火车正从拐角处驶来。

sentences.name: 句子115
sentences.correct: I really wasn't thinking.
sentences.translate: 我真的没在想。

sentences.name: 句子116
sentences.correct: W: What an amazing story!
sentences.translate: W： 多么精彩的故事啊！

sentences.name: 句子117
sentences.correct: Thank you very much.
sentences.translate: 非常感谢你。

sentences.name: 句子118
sentences.correct: Questions 12 to 15 are based on the conversation you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题12至15基于你刚才听到的对话。

sentences.name: 第 12 题 119
sentences.correct: 12. What did Kerry Burke from New York Daily News say about the man?
sentences.translate: 12.《纽约每日新闻》的Kerry Burke对这个男人说了什么？

sentences.name: 第 13 题 120
sentences.correct: 13. What do we learn about the man from the conversation?
sentences.translate: 13.我们从对话中了解到关于这个人的什么？

sentences.name: 第 14 题 121
sentences.correct: 14. What caused the incident?
sentences.translate: 14.事件的起因是什么？

sentences.name: 第 15 题 122
sentences.correct: 15. How did the mother react when the incident occurred?
sentences.translate: 15.事件发生时，母亲的反应如何？

sentences.name: C 部分题干123
sentences.correct: Section C Directions: In this section, you will hear three passages.
sentences.translate: C节说明：在本节中，你将听到三段。

sentences.name: C 部分题干124
sentences.correct: At the end of each passage, you will hear three or four questions.
sentences.translate: 在每篇文章的末尾，你会听到三到四个问题。

sentences.name: C 部分题干125
sentences.correct: Both the passage and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 文章和问题都只讲一次。

sentences.name: C 部分题干126
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。

sentences.name: C 部分题干结束127
sentences.correct: Then mark the corresponding letter on Answer Sheet 1 with a single line through the centre.
sentences.translate: 然后在答题纸1上用一条穿过中心的线标记相应的字母。

sentences.name: 句子128
sentences.correct: Passage One There's one sound that gets a big reaction from kids on a hot day, the sound of an ice-cream truck.
sentences.translate: 在炎热的日子里，有一种声音会引起孩子们的强烈反应，那就是冰淇淋车的声音。

sentences.name: 句子129
sentences.correct: Maria McCartney has been in the mobile ice-cream business since 2005.
sentences.translate: 玛丽亚·麦卡特尼自2005年以来一直从事移动冰淇淋业务。

sentences.name: 句子130
sentences.correct: “When I was a little girl, I saw an ice-cream truck and knew I wanted to have one someday,” McCartney said.
sentences.translate: 麦卡特尼说：“当我还是个小女孩的时候，我看到一辆冰淇淋车，就知道我想有一天能拥有一辆。”。

sentences.name: 句子131
sentences.correct: During the hot days of summer, Maria and her daughter drive an ice-cream truck through neighborhoods and parks in Billings.
sentences.translate: 在炎热的夏天，玛丽亚和她的女儿开着一辆冰淇淋车穿过比林斯的社区和公园。

sentences.name: 句子132
sentences.correct: It's not about making money for this former elementary school teacher.
sentences.translate: 这不是为这位前小学老师赚钱。

sentences.name: 句子133
sentences.correct: Rather, she wants to preserve the tradition of the neighborhood ice-cream truck.
sentences.translate: 相反，她想保留社区冰淇淋车的传统。

sentences.name: 句子134
sentences.correct: “Truly my favorite part is to see the kids jumping up and down and they just get so excited.
sentences.translate: “真的，我最喜欢的部分是看到孩子们跳上跳下，他们太兴奋了。

sentences.name: 句子135
sentences.correct: It's great to build a memory for them too.
sentences.translate: 为他们建立记忆也很棒。

sentences.name: 句子136
sentences.correct: There are not a lot of these ice-cream trucks around anymore.
sentences.translate: 周围的冰淇淋车已经不多了。

sentences.name: 句子137
sentences.correct: The parents come out barefoot and screaming, ready to buy ice-cream; they remember when they were kids and they saw a truck,” she said.
sentences.translate: 父母赤脚尖叫着出来，准备买冰淇淋；他们记得小时候看到一辆卡车，”她说。

sentences.name: 句子138
sentences.correct: While the treats may be ice-cold, Maria has a warm heart for little faces.
sentences.translate: 虽然食物可能很冷，但玛丽亚对小脸有一颗温暖的心。

sentences.name: 句子139
sentences.correct: Her truck features a donation bucket for kids who don't have money for ice-cream.
sentences.translate: 她的卡车上有一个捐款桶，专门为没有钱买冰淇淋的孩子们准备。

sentences.name: 句子140
sentences.correct: “When there are three kids and only two of them have money, I always make sure the third one gets something because I can't drive away and have that third one not have something,” she said.
sentences.translate: 她说：“当有三个孩子，其中只有两个有钱时，我总是确保第三个孩子能得到一些东西，因为我不能开车离开，让第三个没有东西。”。

sentences.name: 句子141
sentences.correct: Questions 16 to 18 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答问题16至18。

sentences.name: 第 16 题 142
sentences.correct: 16. What does the speaker say about Maria McCartney?
sentences.translate: 16.演讲者对玛丽亚·麦卡特尼说了什么？

sentences.name: 第 17 题 143
sentences.correct: 17. Why does Maria go into the mobile ice-cream business?
sentences.translate: 17.玛丽亚为什么要从事移动冰淇淋业务？

sentences.name: 第 18 题 144
sentences.correct: 18. Why does Maria put a donation bucket in her truck?
sentences.translate: 18.为什么玛丽亚把捐款桶放在她的卡车上？

sentences.name: 句子145
sentences.correct: Passage Two We know we have to pay for what we get.
sentences.translate: 我们知道我们必须为我们所得到的付出代价。

sentences.name: 句子146
sentences.correct: If we buy food, we have to pay for it.
sentences.translate: 如果我们买食物，我们必须付钱。

sentences.name: 句子147
sentences.correct: If a doctor treats us, we know there will be a bill to pay.
sentences.translate: 如果医生给我们治疗，我们知道会有账单要付。

sentences.name: 句子148
sentences.correct: These are private bills.
sentences.translate: 这些是私人账单。

sentences.name: 句子149
sentences.correct: But there are also public bills to be paid.
sentences.translate: 但也有公共账单需要支付。

sentences.name: 句子150
sentences.correct: They are paid by the government.
sentences.translate: 他们由政府支付。

sentences.name: 句子151
sentences.correct: In turn we get the needed services.
sentences.translate: 反过来，我们得到了所需的服务。

sentences.name: 句子152
sentences.correct: We pay for these services through taxes.
sentences.translate: 我们通过税收支付这些服务。

sentences.name: 句子153
sentences.correct: What would happen if everyone stopped paying taxes?
sentences.translate: 如果每个人都停止纳税，会发生什么？

sentences.name: 句子154
sentences.correct: The water supply would stop; the streets might not be cleaned; schools would be closed.
sentences.translate: 供水将停止；街道可能没有打扫干净；学校将被关闭。

sentences.name: 句子155
sentences.correct: We would not want to live in such a city.
sentences.translate: 我们不想住在这样的城市。

sentences.name: 句子156
sentences.correct: The chief duty of every government is to protect persons and property.
sentences.translate: 每个政府的首要职责是保护人身和财产。

sentences.name: 句子157
sentences.correct: More than three-fourths of government expenses are used for this purpose.
sentences.translate: 超过四分之三的政府开支用于此目的。

sentences.name: 句子158
sentences.correct: The next largest amount of public money goes to teach and train our citizens.
sentences.translate: 第二大数额的公共资金用于教育和培训我们的公民。

sentences.name: 句子159
sentences.correct: Billions of dollars each year are spent on schools and libraries.
sentences.translate: 每年数十亿美元用于学校和图书馆。

sentences.name: 句子160
sentences.correct: Also, a large amount of public funds is spent on roads.
sentences.translate: 此外，大量公共资金用于道路建设。

sentences.name: 句子161
sentences.correct: Most of the needed funds is raised by taxes.
sentences.translate: 大部分所需资金是通过税收筹集的。

sentences.name: 句子162
sentences.correct: The law orders us to pay taxes.
sentences.translate: 法律要求我们纳税。

sentences.name: 句子163
sentences.correct: We have no choice in the matter.
sentences.translate: 在这件事上我们别无选择。

sentences.name: 句子164
sentences.correct: Years ago the government made money by selling public lands.
sentences.translate: 几年前，政府通过出售公共土地赚钱。

sentences.name: 句子165
sentences.correct: But most of the best public lands have now been sold.
sentences.translate: 但大多数最好的公共土地现在都已被出售。

sentences.name: 句子166
sentences.correct: There are still some public lands that contain oil, coal and other natural resources.
sentences.translate: 仍有一些公共土地含有石油、煤炭和其他自然资源。

sentences.name: 句子167
sentences.correct: They could be sold, but we want to save them for future years.
sentences.translate: 它们可以出售，但我们想把它们留到未来几年。

sentences.name: 句子168
sentences.correct: So we all must pay our share for the services that make our lives comfortable.
sentences.translate: 因此，我们都必须为使我们的生活舒适的服务支付自己的份额。

sentences.name: 句子169
sentences.correct: Questions 19 to 21 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答19至21题。

sentences.name: 第 19 题 170
sentences.correct: 19. What does the speaker mainly talk about?
sentences.translate: 19.演讲者主要谈论什么？

sentences.name: 第 20 题 171
sentences.correct: 20. What is most of the government money used for?
sentences.translate: 20.政府的大部分资金用于什么？

sentences.name: 第 21 题 172
sentences.correct: 21. How did the government raise money to pay public bills in the past?
sentences.translate: 21.政府过去是如何筹集资金支付公共账单的？

sentences.name: 句子173
sentences.correct: Passage Three Did you know that, besides larger places like France and Germany, Europe is home to several extremely tiny countries?
sentences.translate: 你知道吗，除了法国和德国这样的大国，欧洲还有几个非常小的国家？

sentences.name: 句子174
sentences.correct: One of these countries contains less than a square mile of land.
sentences.translate: 其中一个国家的土地面积不到一平方英里。

sentences.name: 句子175
sentences.correct: Another is surrounded on all sides by Italy.
sentences.translate: 另一个被意大利四面包围。

sentences.name: 句子176
sentences.correct: Yet each is an independent land, with its own government, trade, and customs.
sentences.translate: 然而，每个国家都是一片独立的土地，有自己的政府、贸易和海关。

sentences.name: 句子177
sentences.correct: One of the best known of these small countries is Monaco.
sentences.translate: 其中最著名的小国之一是摩纳哥。

sentences.name: 句子178
sentences.correct: It is situated on the Mediterranean Sea and surrounded by France on three sides.
sentences.translate: 它位于地中海沿岸，三面被法国环绕。

sentences.name: 句子179
sentences.correct: Monaco became familiar to Americans when its ruler, Prince Rainier, married the American actress Grace Kelly.
sentences.translate: 当摩纳哥的统治者兰尼埃王子嫁给美国女演员格蕾丝·凯利时，摩纳哥对美国人来说就很熟悉了。

sentences.name: 句子180
sentences.correct: Rainier's family has ruled Monaco almost continuously since 1297.
sentences.translate: 自1297年以来，雷尼尔家族几乎一直统治着摩纳哥。

sentences.name: 句子181
sentences.correct: The land has been independent for over three hundred years.
sentences.translate: 这片土地已经独立了三百多年。

sentences.name: 句子182
sentences.correct: Andorra, with an area of some 200 square miles, is considerably larger than Monaco.
sentences.translate: 安道尔的面积约为200平方英里，比摩纳哥大得多。

sentences.name: 句子183
sentences.correct: This country is located in the Pyrenees Mountains, with France on one side and Spain on the other.

sentences.name: 句子185

sentences.name: 句子187

sentences.name: 句子188
sentences.correct: Liechtenstein uses the same money as its neighbor Switzerland, but it has been an independent country since the 1860s.

sentences.name: 句子189
sentences.correct: Taxes are low, so many businesses have their headquarters here.

sentences.name: 句子190

sentences.name: 句子191
sentences.correct: Other small, independent states in Europe are San Marino and Luxembourg.

sentences.name: 句子192
sentences.correct: Each of these has unique qualities as well.

sentences.name: 句子6
sentences.correct: News Report One A 16th century castle in Scotland is close to collapsing after lumps of soil were washed away by floods, threatening its foundations.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道一：苏格兰一座16世纪的城堡因洪水冲走大块土壤，威胁到其地基，濒临倒塌。

sentences.name: 句子7
sentences.correct: On Sunday, the castle's owner John Gordon, 76, was forced to move out of his property after the River Dee swept away about 60 feet of land, leaving the castle dangerously close to the river, according to the Scottish Daily Record.
sentences.translate: 据《苏格兰每日记录》报道，周日，迪伊河冲走了约60英尺的土地，使城堡危险地靠近河流，76岁的城堡主人约翰·戈登被迫搬出他的房产。

sentences.name: 句子8
sentences.correct: Abergeldie Castle, located in Aberdeenshire,Scotland, was built by Sir Alexander Gordon of Midmar who later became the Earl of Huntly.
sentences.translate: 阿伯格尔迪城堡位于苏格兰阿伯丁郡，由后来成为亨特利伯爵的米德马尔的亚历山大·戈登爵士建造。

sentences.name: 句子9
sentences.correct: The castle, which is located on 11,700 acres, was leased to members of the royal family between 1848 and 1970, including King Edward VII and George V.
sentences.translate: 这座城堡占地11700英亩，在1848年至1970年间租给了皇室成员，包括爱德华七世和乔治五世。

sentences.name: 句子10
sentences.correct: The Scottish Environment Protection Agency has issued more than 35 flood warnings covering several regions, as Scotland continues to clean up after Storm Frank hit the country last Wednesday.
sentences.translate: 苏格兰环境保护局已经发布了覆盖多个地区的35次洪水警报，因为苏格兰在上周三弗兰克风暴袭击该国后仍在继续清理。

sentences.name: 句子11
sentences.correct: “This means that rivers will rise more slowly, but then stay high for much longer,” the environmental agency said.
sentences.translate: 环保局表示：“这意味着河流的水位上升速度会更慢，但随后会在更长时间内保持高位。”。

sentences.name: 句子12

sentences.name: 第 1 题 13

sentences.name: 句子15
sentences.correct: News Report Two Rescue efforts were underway Thursday morning for 17 miners who were stuck in an elevator below ground at Cargill rock salt mine near Lansing, New York, according to Marcia Lynch, public information officer with Tompkins County's emergency response department.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道汤普金斯县应急响应部门的公共信息官Marcia Lynch表示，周四上午，在纽约兰辛附近的嘉吉岩盐矿，17名矿工被困在地下电梯中，救援工作正在进行中。

sentences.name: 句子16
sentences.correct: Emergency workers have made contact with the miners via a radio, and they all appear to be uninjured, said Jessica Verfuss, the emergency department's assistant director.
sentences.translate: 急救人员已通过无线电与矿工取得联系，他们似乎都没有受伤，急救部门助理主任Jessica Verfuss说。

sentences.name: 句子17
sentences.correct: Crews have managed to provide heat packs and blankets to the miners so that they can keep warm during the rescue operation, Verfuss said.
sentences.translate: Verfuss说，工作人员设法为矿工提供了隔热包和毯子，以便他们在救援行动中保持温暖。

sentences.name: 句子18
sentences.correct: Details about what led to the workers' being trapped in the elevator weren't immediately available.
sentences.translate: 关于导致工人被困在电梯里的原因的详细信息尚不清楚。

sentences.name: 句子19
sentences.correct: The mine, along New York's Cayuga Lake, processes salt used for road treatment.
sentences.translate: 该矿位于纽约卡尤加湖沿岸，加工用于道路处理的盐。

sentences.name: 句子20
sentences.correct: It produces about 2 million tons of salt that is shipped to more than 1,500 places in the northeastern United States.
sentences.translate: 它生产约200万吨盐，运往美国东北部的1500多个地方。

sentences.name: 句子21
sentences.correct: The rock salt mine is one of three operated by Cargill, with the other two in Louisiana and Ohio.
sentences.translate: 该岩盐矿是嘉吉公司经营的三个岩盐矿之一，另外两个位于路易斯安那州和俄亥俄州。

sentences.name: 句子22
sentences.correct: Questions 3 and 4 are based on the news report you have just heard.

sentences.name: 第 3 题 23

sentences.translate: 3.新闻报道对盐矿工人说了什么？

sentences.name: 第 4 题 24
sentences.correct: 4. What did the rescue team do?
sentences.translate: 4.救援队做了什么？

sentences.name: 句子25
sentences.correct: News Report Three The US Postal Service announced today that it is considering closing about 3 700 post offices over the next year because of falling revenues.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道三美国邮政局今天宣布，由于收入下降，它正在考虑在明年关闭约3700家邮局。

sentences.name: 句子26
sentences.correct: Facing an $8.3 billion budget deficit this year, closing post offices is one of several proposals the Postal Service has put forth recently to cut costs.
sentences.translate: 面对今年83亿美元的预算赤字，关闭邮局是邮政服务最近提出的削减成本的几项建议之一。

sentences.name: 句子27
sentences.correct: Last week, for example, Postmaster General Pat Donahoe announced plans to stop mail delivery on Saturdays, a move he says could save $3 billion annually.
sentences.translate: 例如，上周，邮政局长Pat Donahoe宣布计划停止在周六投递邮件，他说此举每年可以节省30亿美元。

sentences.name: 句子28
sentences.correct: “We are losing revenue as we speak,” Donahoe said.“We do not want taxpayer money.
sentences.translate: 多纳霍说：“就在我们说话的时候，我们正在失去收入。”。“我们不需要纳税人的钱。

sentences.name: 句子29
sentences.correct: We want to be self-sufficient.
sentences.translate: 我们希望自给自足。

sentences.name: 句子30
sentences.correct: So like any other business you have to make choices.” Dean Granholm, the vice president for delivery and post office operations, said the first wave of closings would begin this fall.
sentences.translate: 所以，像其他行业一样，你必须做出选择。”负责快递和邮局运营的副总裁Dean Granholm表示，第一波关闭将于今年秋天开始。

sentences.name: 句子31
sentences.correct: He estimated that about 3,000 postmasters, 500 station managers and between 500 and 1,000 postal clerks could lose their jobs.
sentences.translate: 他估计，大约3000名邮政局长、500名车站经理和500至1000名邮政职员可能会失业。

sentences.name: 句子32
sentences.correct: Questions 5 to 7 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的新闻报道，回答问题5至7。

sentences.name: 第 5 题 33
sentences.correct: 5. What is the US Postal Service planning to do?
sentences.translate: 5.美国邮政局计划做什么？

sentences.name: 第 6 题 34
sentences.correct: 6. What measure has been planned to save costs?
sentences.translate: 6.计划采取什么措施来节省成本？

sentences.name: 第 7 题 35

sentences.translate: 7.拟议措施生效后会发生什么？

sentences.name: B 部分题干36
sentences.correct: Section B Directions: In this section, you will hear two long conversations.
sentences.translate: B部分说明：在本节中，您将听到两段长对话。

sentences.name: B 部分题干37
sentences.correct: At the end of each conversation, you will hear four questions.

sentences.name: B 部分题干38

sentences.name: B 部分题干39
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).

sentences.name: 句子41
sentences.correct: Conversation One M: Mrs.Hampton, we've got trouble in the press room this morning.
sentences.translate: 对话一M：汉普顿太太，我们今天早上在新闻发布室遇到了麻烦。

sentences.name: 句子42
sentences.correct: W: Oh dear. What about?
sentences.translate: W： 哦，天哪。怎么样？

sentences.name: 句子43
sentences.correct: M: One of the press operators arrived an hour and a half late.
sentences.translate: M： 一名报务员迟到了一个半小时。

sentences.name: 句子44
sentences.correct: W: But that's a straightforward affair.
sentences.translate: W： 但这是一件直截了当的事情。

sentences.name: 句子45
sentences.correct: He will simply lose part of his pay.
sentences.translate: 他只会损失一部分工资。

sentences.name: 句子46
sentences.correct: That's why we have a clock-in system.
sentences.translate: 这就是为什么我们在系统中有一个时钟。

sentences.name: 句子47
sentences.correct: M: But the point is the man was clocked in at 8 o'clock.
sentences.translate: M： 但问题是，这名男子是在8点钟打卡的。

sentences.name: 句子48
sentences.correct: We have John standing by the time clock, and he swears he saw nothing irregular.
sentences.translate: 我们让约翰站在时钟旁，他发誓他没有看到任何异常。

sentences.name: 句子49
sentences.correct: W: Is John reliable?
sentences.translate: W： 约翰可靠吗？

sentences.name: 句子50
sentences.correct: M: Yes, he is.
sentences.translate: M： 是的，他是。

sentences.name: 句子51
sentences.correct: That's why we chose him for the job.
sentences.translate: 这就是为什么我们选择他做这份工作。

sentences.name: 句子52
sentences.correct: W: Have you spoken to the man who was late?
sentences.translate: W： 你和迟到的那个人谈过了吗？

sentences.name: 句子53
sentences.correct: M: Not yet.
sentences.translate: M： 还没有。

sentences.name: 句子54
sentences.correct: I thought I'd have a word with you first.
sentences.translate: 我想先和你谈谈。

sentences.name: 句子55
sentences.correct: He's a difficult man, and I think there's been some trouble on the shop floor.
sentences.translate: 他是个难相处的人，我觉得车间出了点问题。

sentences.name: 句子56
sentences.correct: I've got a feeling that the trade union representative is behind this.
sentences.translate: 我有一种感觉，工会代表是幕后黑手。

sentences.name: 句子57
sentences.correct: The manager told me that Jack Green's been very active around the shop the last few days.
sentences.translate: 经理告诉我，杰克·格林最近几天在店里很活跃。

sentences.name: 句子58
sentences.correct: W: Well, what do you want me to do?
sentences.translate: W： 好吧，你想让我做什么？

sentences.name: 句子59
sentences.correct: M: I was wondering if you'd see Smith— the man who was late— because you are so much better at handling things like this.
sentences.translate: M： 我想知道你是否能见见史密斯——那个迟到的人——因为你更擅长处理这样的事情。

sentences.name: 句子60
sentences.correct: W: Oh, alright.
sentences.translate: W： 哦，好吧。

sentences.name: 句子61
sentences.correct: I'll see him.
sentences.translate: 我会去见他的。

sentences.name: 句子62
sentences.correct: I must say I agree with you about there being bad feelings in the works.
sentences.translate: 我必须说，我同意你的观点，作品中有不好的感觉。

sentences.name: 句子63
sentences.correct: I've had the idea for some time that Jack Green's been busy stirring things up in connection with the latest wage claim.
sentences.translate: 一段时间以来，我一直认为杰克·格林一直在忙着挑起与最新工资索赔有关的事情。

sentences.name: 句子64
sentences.correct: He's always trying to make trouble.
sentences.translate: 他总是试图制造麻烦。

sentences.name: 句子65
sentences.correct: Well, I'll get the manager to send Smith up here.
sentences.translate: 好吧，我会让经理派史密斯上来的。

sentences.name: 句子66
sentences.correct: Questions 8 to 11 are based on the conversation you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题8至11基于你刚才听到的对话。

sentences.name: 第 8 题 67
sentences.correct: 8. What will happen to the press operator who was late for work according to the woman?
sentences.translate: 8.据这位女士说，上班迟到的新闻操作员会怎么样？

sentences.name: 第 9 题 68
sentences.correct: 9. What does the man say about John who stands by the time clock?
sentences.translate: 9.站在钟旁的那个人怎么评价约翰？

sentences.name: 第 10 题 69
sentences.correct: 10. Why does the man suggest the woman see the worker who was late?
sentences.translate: 10.为什么男人建议女人去见迟到的工人？

sentences.translate: 11.这位女士怎么评价杰克·格林？

sentences.name: 句子71
sentences.correct: Conversation Two W: Our topic today is about something that foreigners nearly always say when they visit Britain.
sentences.translate: 对话二W：我们今天的主题是外国人访问英国时几乎总是说的话。

sentences.name: 句子72
sentences.correct: It's “Why are the British so cold?” And they're talking about the British personality— the famous British “reserve”.
sentences.translate: 这是“为什么英国人这么冷？”他们谈论的是英国人的性格——著名的英国“矜持”。

sentences.name: 句子73
sentences.correct: It means that we aren't very friendly.
sentences.translate: 这意味着我们不是很友好。

sentences.name: 句子74
sentences.correct: We aren't very open.
sentences.translate: 我们不是很开放。

sentences.name: 句子75
sentences.correct: M: So do you think it's true?
sentences.translate: M： 你认为这是真的吗？

sentences.name: 句子76
sentences.correct: W: It's a difficult one.
sentences.translate: W： 这很难。

sentences.name: 句子77
sentences.correct: So many people who visit Britain say it's difficult to make friends with British people.
sentences.translate: 很多访问英国的人都说很难和英国人交朋友。

sentences.name: 句子78
sentences.correct: They say we're cold, reserved, unfriendly...
sentences.translate: 他们说我们冷漠、保守、不友好。。。

sentences.name: 句子79
sentences.correct: M: I think it's true.
sentences.translate: M： 我认为这是真的。

sentences.name: 句子80
sentences.correct: Look at Americans or Australians.
sentences.translate: 看看美国人或澳大利亚人。

sentences.name: 句子81
sentences.correct: They speak the same language, but they're much more open.
sentences.translate: 他们说同样的语言，但他们更开放。

sentences.name: 句子82
sentences.correct: And you see it when you travel.
sentences.translate: 当你旅行时，你会看到它。

sentences.name: 句子83
sentences.correct: People—I mean strangers— speak to you on the street or on the train.
sentences.translate: 人们——我是说陌生人——在街上或火车上和你说话。

sentences.name: 句子84
sentences.correct: British people seldom speak on the train, or the bus.
sentences.translate: 英国人很少在火车或公共汽车上说话。

sentences.name: 句子85
sentences.correct: Not in London, anyway.
sentences.translate: 不是在伦敦，无论如何。

sentences.name: 句子86
sentences.correct: W: “Not in London.” That's it.
sentences.translate: W： “不在伦敦。”就是这样。

sentences.name: 句子87
sentences.correct: Capital cities are full of tourists and are never friendly.
sentences.translate: 首都城市到处都是游客，从来都不友好。

sentences.name: 句子88
sentences.correct: People are different in other parts of the country.
sentences.translate: 这个国家其他地区的人不一样。

sentences.name: 句子89
sentences.correct: M: Not completely.
sentences.translate: M： 不完全。

sentences.name: 句子90
sentences.correct: I met a woman once, an Italian.
sentences.translate: 我曾经见过一个女人，一个意大利人。

sentences.name: 句子91
sentences.correct: She'd been working in Manchester for two years, and no one— not one of her colleagues— had ever invited her to their home.
sentences.translate: 她在曼彻斯特工作了两年，没有人——包括她的同事——邀请她到他们家。

sentences.name: 句子92
sentences.correct: They were friendly to her at work, but nothing else.
sentences.translate: 他们在工作中对她很友好，但除此之外什么都没有。

sentences.name: 句子93
sentences.correct: She couldn't believe it.
sentences.translate: 她简直不敢相信。

sentences.name: 句子94
sentences.correct: She said that would never happen in Italy.
sentences.translate: 她说这在意大利永远不会发生。

sentences.name: 句子95
sentences.correct: W: You know what they say— “an Englishman's home is his castle”.
sentences.translate: W： 你知道他们说什么吗——“英国人的家就是他的城堡”。

sentences.name: 句子96
sentences.correct: It's really difficult to get inside.
sentences.translate: 进去真的很难。

sentences.name: 句子97
sentences.correct: M: Yeah. It's about being private.
sentences.translate: M： 是啊。这关乎隐私。

sentences.name: 句子98
sentences.correct: You go home to your house and your garden and you close the door.
sentences.translate: 你回到你的房子和花园，然后关上门。

sentences.name: 句子99
sentences.correct: It's your place.
sentences.translate: 这是你的地方。

sentences.name: 句子100
sentences.correct: W: That's why the British don't like flats.
sentences.translate: W： 这就是为什么英国人不喜欢公寓。

sentences.name: 句子101
sentences.correct: They prefer to live in houses.
sentences.translate: 他们更喜欢住在房子里。

sentences.name: 句子102
sentences.correct: M: That's true.
sentences.translate: M： 确实如此。

sentences.name: 句子103
sentences.correct: Questions 12 to 15 are based on the conversation you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题12至15基于你刚才听到的对话。

sentences.name: 第 12 题 104
sentences.correct: 12. What do foreigners generally think of British people according to the woman?
sentences.translate: 12.根据这位女士的说法，外国人通常对英国人有什么看法？

sentences.name: 第 13 题 105
sentences.correct: 13. What may British people typically do on a train according to the man?
sentences.translate: 13.根据这位男士的说法，英国人在火车上通常会做什么？

sentences.name: 第 14 题 106
sentences.correct: 14. What does the man say about the Italian woman working in Manchester?
sentences.translate: 14.这位男士对在曼彻斯特工作的意大利女性有何评价？

sentences.name: 第 15 题 107
sentences.correct: 15. Why do British people prefer houses to flats?
sentences.translate: 15.为什么英国人更喜欢房子而不是公寓？

sentences.name: C 部分题干108
sentences.correct: Section C Directions: In this section, you will hear three passages.
sentences.translate: C节说明：在本节中，你将听到三段。

sentences.name: C 部分题干109
sentences.correct: At the end of each passage, you will hear three or four questions.
sentences.translate: 在每篇文章的末尾，你会听到三到四个问题。

sentences.name: C 部分题干110
sentences.correct: Both the passage and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 文章和问题都只讲一次。

sentences.name: C 部分题干111
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。

sentences.name: C 部分题干结束112

sentences.translate: 然后在答题纸1上用一条穿过中心的线标记相应的字母。

sentences.name: 句子113
sentences.correct: Passage One In college, time is scarce, and consequently, very precious.
sentences.translate: 在大学里，时间很稀缺，因此非常宝贵。

sentences.name: 句子114
sentences.correct: At the same time, expenses in college pile up surprisingly quickly.
sentences.translate: 与此同时，大学的开支惊人地迅速增加。

sentences.name: 句子115
sentences.correct: A part-time job is a good way to balance costs while ensuring there is enough time left over for both academic subjects and after-class activities.
sentences.translate: 兼职工作是平衡成本的好方法，同时确保有足够的时间用于学术科目和课外活动。

sentences.name: 句子116
sentences.correct: If you are a college student looking for a part-time job, the best place to start your job search is right on campus.
sentences.translate: 如果你是一名正在寻找兼职工作的大学生，那么开始求职的最佳地点就是校园。

sentences.name: 句子117
sentences.correct: There are tons of on-campus job opportunities, and as a student, you'll automatically be given hiring priority.
sentences.translate: 校园里有很多工作机会，作为一名学生，你会自动获得招聘优先权。

sentences.name: 句子118
sentences.correct: Plus, on-campus jobs eliminate commuting time, and could be a great way to connect with academic and professional resources at your university.
sentences.translate: 此外，校内工作消除了通勤时间，这可能是与大学学术和专业资源联系的好方法。

sentences.name: 句子119
sentences.correct: Check with your school's careers service or employment office for help to find a campus job.
sentences.translate: 向学校的职业服务或就业办公室寻求帮助，以找到校园工作。

sentences.name: 句子120
sentences.correct: Of course, there are opportunities for part-time work off-campus, too.
sentences.translate: 当然，校外也有兼职工作的机会。

sentences.name: 句子121
sentences.correct: If you spend a little time digging for the right part-time jobs, you'll save yourself time when you find a job that leaves you with enough time to get your schoolwork done, too.
sentences.translate: 如果你花一点时间寻找合适的兼职工作，当你找到一份能让你有足够时间完成学业的工作时，你会节省自己的时间。

sentences.name: 句子122
sentences.correct: If you are a college student looking for work but worried you won't have enough time to devote to academic subjects, consider working as a study hall or library monitor.
sentences.translate: 如果你是一名大学生，正在找工作，但担心没有足够的时间专注于学术科目，可以考虑当自习室或图书馆管理员。

sentences.name: 句子123
sentences.correct: Responsibilities generally include supervising study spaces to ensure that a quiet atmosphere is maintained.
sentences.translate: 职责通常包括监督学习空间，以确保保持安静的氛围。

sentences.name: 句子124
sentences.correct: It's a pretty easy job, but one with lots of downtime— which means you'll have plenty of time to catch up on reading, do homework or study for an exam.
sentences.translate: 这是一项相当容易的工作，但需要大量的休息时间——这意味着你有足够的时间赶上阅读、做作业或为考试学习。

sentences.name: 句子125
sentences.correct: Questions 16 to 18 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答问题16至18。

sentences.name: 第 16 题 126
sentences.correct: 16. What does the speaker say about college students applying for on-campus jobs?
sentences.translate: 16.演讲者对大学生申请校内工作有什么看法？

sentences.name: 第 17 题 127
sentences.correct: 17. What can students do to find a campus job according to the speaker?
sentences.translate: 17.根据演讲者的说法，学生可以做些什么来找到校园工作？

sentences.name: 第 18 题 128
sentences.correct: 18. What does the speaker say is a library monitor's responsibility?
sentences.translate: 18.演讲者说图书馆监督员的职责是什么？

sentences.name: 句子129
sentences.correct: Passage Two Agricultural workers in green tea fields near Mt.Kenya are gathering the tea leaves.
sentences.translate: 肯尼亚山附近的绿茶田中，两名农业工人正在采摘茶叶。

sentences.name: 句子130
sentences.correct: It is beautiful to see.
sentences.translate: 这真是美不胜收。

sentences.name: 句子131
sentences.correct: The rows of tea bushes are straight.
sentences.translate: 成排的茶树是直的。

sentences.name: 句子132
sentences.correct: All appears to be well.
sentences.translate: 一切似乎都很好。

sentences.name: 句子133
sentences.correct: But the farmers who planted the bushes are worried.
sentences.translate: 但种植灌木的农民们很担心。

sentences.name: 句子134
sentences.correct: Nelson Kibara is one of them.
sentences.translate: Nelson Kibara就是其中之一。

sentences.name: 句子135
sentences.correct: He has been growing tea in the Kerugoya area for 40 years.
sentences.translate: 他在Kerugoya地区种植茶叶已有40年。

sentences.name: 句子136
sentences.correct: He says the prices this year have been so low that he has made almost no profit.
sentences.translate: 他说，今年的价格太低了，他几乎没有盈利。

sentences.name: 句子137
sentences.correct: He says he must grow different kinds of tea if he is to survive.
sentences.translate: 他说，如果他想生存下去，就必须种植不同种类的茶。

sentences.name: 句子138
sentences.correct: Mr.Kibara and hundreds of other farmers have been removing some of their tea bushes and planting a new kind of tea developed by the Tea Research Foundation of Kenya.
sentences.translate: Kibara先生和其他数百名农民一直在移除他们的一些茶树，种植一种由肯尼亚茶叶研究基金会开发的新型茶叶。

sentences.name: 句子139
sentences.correct: Its leaves are purple and brown.
sentences.translate: 它的叶子是紫色和棕色的。

sentences.name: 句子140
sentences.correct: When the tea is boiled, the drink has a purple color.
sentences.translate: 当茶煮沸时，饮料呈紫色。

sentences.name: 句子141
sentences.correct: Medical researchers have studied the health benefits of the new tea.
sentences.translate: 医学研究人员研究了这种新茶的健康益处。

sentences.name: 句子142
sentences.correct: They say it is healthier than green tea and could be sold for a price that is three to four times higher than the price of green tea.
sentences.translate: 他们说，它比绿茶更健康，售价可能比绿茶高出三到四倍。

sentences.name: 句子143
sentences.correct: But Mr.Kibara says he has not received a higher price for his purple tea crop.
sentences.translate: 但Kibara先生表示，他的紫茶作物还没有收到更高的价格。

sentences.name: 句子144
sentences.correct: He says the market for the tea is unstable.
sentences.translate: 他说，茶叶市场不稳定。

sentences.name: 句子145
sentences.correct: And he is often forced to sell his purple tea for the same price as green tea leaves.
sentences.translate: 他经常被迫以与绿茶相同的价格出售他的紫茶。

sentences.name: 句子146
sentences.correct: He says there are not enough buyers willing to pay more for the purple tea.
sentences.translate: 他说，没有足够的买家愿意为紫茶支付更高的价格。

sentences.name: 第 19 题 147
sentences.correct: Questions 19 to 21 are based on the passage you have just heard 19. Why have tea farmers in Kenya decided to grow purple tea?
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答19至21题。为什么肯尼亚的茶农决定种植紫茶？

sentences.name: 第 20 题 148
sentences.correct: 20. What do researchers say about purple tea?
sentences.translate: 20.研究人员对紫茶有什么看法？

sentences.name: 第 21 题 149
sentences.correct: 21. What does Mr.Kibara find about purple tea?
sentences.translate: 21.Kibara先生对紫茶有什么看法？

sentences.name: 句子150
sentences.correct: Passage Three Today's consumers want beautiful handcrafted objects to wear and to have for their home environment.
sentences.translate: 第三段今天的消费者想要漂亮的手工制品来佩戴，并为他们的家庭环境做好准备。

sentences.name: 句子151
sentences.correct: They prefer something unique and they demand quality.
sentences.translate: 他们喜欢独特的东西，他们要求质量。

sentences.name: 句子152
sentences.correct: Craftsmen today are meeting this demand.
sentences.translate: 今天的工匠们正在满足这一需求。

sentences.name: 句子153
sentences.correct: People and homes are showing great change as more and more unique handcrafted items become available.
sentences.translate: 随着越来越多独特的手工制品的出现，人们和家庭都发生了巨大的变化。

sentences.name: 句子154
sentences.correct: Handicrafts are big business.
sentences.translate: 手工艺品是大生意。

sentences.name: 句子155
sentences.correct: No longer does a good craftsman have to work in a job he dislikes all day, and then try to create at night.
sentences.translate: 一个好的工匠不再需要整天做他不喜欢的工作，然后在晚上尝试创作。

sentences.name: 句子156
sentences.correct: He has earned his professional status.
sentences.translate: 他已经赢得了职业地位。

sentences.name: 句子157
sentences.correct: He is now a respected member of society.
sentences.translate: 他现在是社会上受人尊敬的一员。

sentences.name: 句子158
sentences.correct: Part of the fun of being a craftsman is meeting other craftsmen.
sentences.translate: 成为一名工匠的乐趣之一就是结识其他工匠。

sentences.name: 句子159
sentences.correct: They love to share their ideas and materials and help others find markets for their work.
sentences.translate: 他们喜欢分享自己的想法和材料，并帮助他人为自己的作品找到市场。

sentences.name: 句子160
sentences.correct: Craftsmen have helped educate consumers to make wise choices.
sentences.translate: 工匠们帮助教育消费者做出明智的选择。

sentences.name: 句子161
sentences.correct: They help them become aware of design and technique.
sentences.translate: 他们帮助他们了解设计和技术。

sentences.name: 句子162
sentences.correct: They help them relate their choice to its intended use.
sentences.translate: 他们帮助他们将自己的选择与预期用途联系起来。

sentences.name: 句子163
sentences.correct: They often involve consumers in trying the craft themselves.
sentences.translate: 他们经常让消费者自己尝试这种工艺。

sentences.name: 句子164
sentences.correct: When a group of craftsmen expands to include more members, a small craft organization is formed.
sentences.translate: 当一群工匠扩大到包括更多的成员时，就会形成一个小型的手工艺组织。

sentences.name: 句子165
sentences.correct: Such an organization does a lot in training workshops in special media, crafts marketing techniques, crafts fairs and sales, festivals, TV appearances and demonstrations.
sentences.translate: 这样一个组织在特殊媒体培训研讨会、工艺品营销技巧、工艺品博览会和销售、节日、电视露面和演示方面做了很多工作。

sentences.name: 句子166
sentences.correct: State art councils help sponsor local arts and crafts festivals which draw crowds of tourist consumers.
sentences.translate: 州艺术委员会帮助赞助当地的工艺品节，吸引了大批旅游消费者。

sentences.name: 句子167
sentences.correct: This boosts the local economy considerably because tourists not only buy crafts, but they also use the restaurants and hotels and other services of the area.
sentences.translate: 这大大促进了当地经济的发展，因为游客不仅购买工艺品，还使用该地区的餐馆、酒店和其他服务。

sentences.name: 句子168
sentences.correct: Questions 22 to 25 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答问题22至25。

sentences.name: 第 22 题 169
sentences.correct: 22. What does the speaker say about today's consumers?
sentences.translate: 22.演讲者对当今的消费者说了什么？

sentences.name: 第 23 题 170
sentences.correct: 23. What does the speaker say about good craftsmen in the past?
sentences.translate: 23.说话者对过去的好工匠说了什么？

sentences.name: 第 24 题 171
sentences.correct: 24. What do craftsmen help consumers do?
sentences.translate: 24.工匠帮助消费者做什么？

sentences.name: 第 25 题 172
sentences.correct: 25. Why do state art councils help sponsor local arts and crafts festivals?
sentences.translate: 25.为什么州艺术委员会帮助赞助当地的艺术和手工艺节？

sentences.name: 句子173
sentences.correct: This is the end of listening comprehension.
sentences.translate: 听力理解到此结束。

sentences.name: A 部分题干1
sentences.correct: Model Test 8 Section A Directions: In this section, you will hear three news reports.
sentences.translate: 模型测试8 A部分说明：在本节中，您将听到三篇新闻报道。

sentences.name: A 部分题干2
sentences.correct: At the end of each news report, you will hear two or three questions.
sentences.translate: 在每一篇新闻报道的结尾，你会听到两三个问题。

sentences.name: A 部分题干3
sentences.correct: Both the news report and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道和提问都只会说一次。

sentences.name: A 部分题干4
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。
