sentences.name: 句子6
sentences.correct: News Report One More than 30 people have been killed by a series of car bombs in the Iraqi capital Baghdad.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道一伊拉克首都巴格达发生一系列汽车炸弹袭击，造成30多人死亡。

sentences.name: 句子7
sentences.correct: Many others were wounded in the explosions which targeted mainly Shiah areas of the city.
sentences.translate: 许多其他人在主要针对该市什叶派地区的爆炸中受伤。

sentences.name: 句子8
sentences.correct: The first suicide bomber targeted a police checkpoint in western Baghdad, killing at least 10 people including several policemen.
sentences.translate: 第一名自杀式炸弹袭击者袭击了巴格达西部的一个警察检查站，造成至少10人死亡，其中包括几名警察。

sentences.name: 句子9
sentences.correct: A second bomb exploded in a busy high street in the Shiah neighborhood, then a third close by.
sentences.translate: 第二枚炸弹在什叶派社区一条繁忙的商业街上爆炸，随后第三枚炸弹在附近爆炸。

sentences.name: 句子10
sentences.correct: People around were wounded severely, which caused great sensation.
sentences.translate: 周围的人受了重伤，引起了极大的轰动。

sentences.name: 句子11
sentences.correct: It is not known who's responsible for the violence.
sentences.translate: 目前尚不清楚谁应对暴力事件负责。

sentences.name: 句子12
sentences.correct: And there have been repeated attacks in Baghdad even before Islamic State forces began their takeover of large parts of Iraq.
sentences.translate: 甚至在伊斯兰国部队开始接管伊拉克大部分地区之前，巴格达就发生了多次袭击。

sentences.name: 句子13
sentences.correct: Officials have now said the government's grip on the western province of Anbar is weak.
sentences.translate: 官员们现在表示，政府对西部安巴尔省的控制很弱。

sentences.name: 句子14
sentences.correct: Questions 1 and 2 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题1和2基于你刚才听到的新闻报道。

sentences.name: 第 1 题 15
sentences.correct: 1. What is the news report mainly about?
sentences.translate: 1.新闻报道的主要内容是什么？

sentences.name: 第 2 题 16
sentences.correct: 2. Where did the second bomb explode?
sentences.translate: 2.第二枚炸弹是在哪里爆炸的？

sentences.name: 句子17
sentences.correct: News Report Two The United States says it will provide an additional 180 million dollars to help feed the people of South Sudan who are threatened by famine.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道二美国表示，将额外提供1.8亿美元，帮助受饥荒威胁的南苏丹人民。

sentences.name: 句子18
sentences.correct: The White House urged the country's president and its former deputy to assume their responsibilities and prevent further needless suffering.
sentences.translate: 白宫敦促该国总统和前副总统承担起责任，防止进一步的不必要痛苦。

sentences.name: 句子19
sentences.correct: Chris Stillwalker from BBC in the United States reports.
sentences.translate: 英国广播公司驻美国记者Chris Stillwalker报道。

sentences.name: 句子20
sentences.correct: “This rises to more than 600 million dollars, added to the amount of the United States.
sentences.translate: “这增加到6亿多美元，加上美国的金额。

sentences.name: 句子21
sentences.correct: The White House says the South Sudanese are suffering because of the inability of the country's leaders to put their people's interests above their own.
sentences.translate: 白宫表示，南苏丹人民正在遭受苦难，因为该国领导人无法将人民的利益置于自己的利益之上。

sentences.name: 句子22
sentences.correct: The power struggle between its President Salva Kiir and his ex-deputy Riek Machar has plunged the country into renewed warfare, leaving thousands dead and nearly two million refugees.” Questions 3 and 4 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 总统萨尔瓦·基尔和他的前副手里克·马查尔之间的权力斗争使该国陷入新的战争，造成数千人死亡，近200万难民。”问题3和4基于你刚才听到的新闻报道。

sentences.name: 第 3 题 23
sentences.correct: 3. What happened to the people of South Sudan?
sentences.translate: 3.南苏丹人民怎么了？

sentences.name: 第 4 题 24
sentences.correct: 4. According to the White House, why are the South Sudanese suffering?
sentences.translate: 4.根据白宫的说法，南苏丹人为什么受苦？

sentences.name: 句子25
sentences.correct: News Report Three Twenty tourists were among the victims of an attack by a gunman at one of Tunisia's most prestigious museums.
sentences.translate: 新闻报道突尼斯最负盛名的博物馆之一遭到枪手袭击，受害者中包括二十名游客。

sentences.name: 句子26
sentences.correct: The attacker shot dead visitors from South Africa, Poland, Italy and Spain as they were getting off a bus outside the Bardo Museum in the capital Tunis which stands next to the country's parliament.
sentences.translate: 袭击者枪杀了来自南非、波兰、意大利和西班牙的游客，当时他们正在首都突尼斯的巴尔多博物馆外下车，该博物馆位于该国议会旁边。

sentences.name: 句子27
sentences.correct: At least 22 people died in the attack and more than 40 others were wounded.
sentences.translate: 袭击中至少有22人死亡，40多人受伤。

sentences.name: 句子28
sentences.correct: Two hours later Tunisian security forces shot the gunman dead.
sentences.translate: 两小时后，突尼斯安全部队开枪打死了枪手。

sentences.name: 句子29
sentences.correct: The last group of tourists were taken away on a bus a while ago, wailing at bystanders and security forces and many Tunisians here are reluctant to leave.
sentences.translate: 不久前，最后一批游客被一辆公共汽车带走，他们向旁观者和安全部队哭诉，这里的许多突尼斯人不愿离开。

sentences.name: 句子30
sentences.correct: The attacker has managed to strike both at political as well at the economic heart of the country.
sentences.translate: 袭击者成功地袭击了该国的政治和经济中心。

sentences.name: 句子31
sentences.correct: The site of the attack，the Bardo Museum, is to Tunis what Louvre is to Paris.
sentences.translate: 袭击发生地巴尔多博物馆对突尼斯来说，就像卢浮宫对巴黎一样。

sentences.name: 句子32
sentences.correct: It's in walking distance to parliament where terrified politicians were locked down when the attack began.
sentences.translate: 它距离议会只有几步之遥，袭击开始时，惊恐的政客们被关在那里。

sentences.name: 句子33
sentences.correct: This is the first attack on civilians in decades.
sentences.translate: 这是几十年来首次针对平民的袭击。

sentences.name: 句子34
sentences.correct: As an act of solidarity with victims, politicians have been gathering this evening.
sentences.translate: 为了声援受害者，政客们今晚聚集在一起。

sentences.name: 句子35
sentences.correct: Questions 5 to 7 are based on the news report you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的新闻报道，回答问题5至7。

sentences.name: 第 5 题 36
sentences.correct: 5. How many people were killed in the attack?
sentences.translate: 5.袭击中有多少人丧生？

sentences.name: 第 6 题 37
sentences.correct: 6. What happened to the gunman?
sentences.translate: 6.枪手怎么了？

sentences.name: 第 7 题 38
sentences.correct: 7. When the attack happened, what did the politicians do?
sentences.translate: 7.袭击发生时，政客们做了什么？

sentences.name: B 部分题干39
sentences.correct: Section B Directions: In this section, you will hear two long conversations.
sentences.translate: B部分说明：在本节中，您将听到两段长对话。

sentences.name: B 部分题干40
sentences.correct: At the end of each conversation, you will hear four questions.
sentences.translate: 在每次对话结束时，您将听到四个问题。

sentences.name: B 部分题干41
sentences.correct: Both the conversation and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 对话和问题只会说一次。

sentences.name: B 部分题干42
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。

sentences.name: B 部分题干结束43
sentences.correct: Then mark the corresponding letter on Answer Sheet 1 with a single line through the centre.
sentences.translate: 然后在答题纸1上用一条穿过中心的线标记相应的字母。

sentences.name: 句子44
sentences.correct: Conversation One W: Hey, Taxi! Great！Thanks for pulling over.
sentences.translate: 对话一女：嘿，出租车！太棒了谢谢你靠边停车。

sentences.name: 句子45
sentences.correct: M: Where to?
sentences.translate: M： 去哪里？

sentences.name: 句子46
sentences.correct: W: I'm going to the National Museum of Art, and...
sentences.translate: W： 我要去国家艺术博物馆，然后。。。

sentences.name: 句子47
sentences.correct: M: Sure. Hop in.
sentences.translate: M： 当然。跳进去。

sentences.name: 句子48
sentences.correct: W: Excuse me, how long does it take to get there?
sentences.translate: W： 打扰一下，到那里需要多长时间？

sentences.name: 句子49
sentences.correct: M: That all depends on the traffic, but it shouldn't take more than 20 minutes for an average driver.
sentences.translate: M： 这一切都取决于交通状况，但对于普通司机来说，这不应该超过20分钟。

sentences.name: 句子50
sentences.correct: And I'm not average.
sentences.translate: 我不是一般人。

sentences.name: 句子51
sentences.correct: I have driving down to an art, so we should be able to cruise through traffic and get there in less than 12 minutes.
sentences.translate: 我要开车去艺术馆，所以我们应该能够在交通堵塞中巡航，在不到12分钟的时间内到达那里。

sentences.name: 句子52
sentences.correct: W: Okay. Sorry for asking, but do you have any idea how much the fare will be?
sentences.translate: W： 好吧。很抱歉问这个问题，但你知道票价是多少吗？

sentences.name: 句子53
sentences.correct: M: It shouldn't be more than 18 dollars...
sentences.translate: M： 不应该超过18美元。。。

sentences.name: 句子54
sentences.correct: not including a tip of course.
sentences.translate: 当然不包括小费。

sentences.name: 句子55
sentences.correct: W: By the way, do you know what time the museum closes?
sentences.translate: W： 顺便问一下，你知道博物馆什么时候关门吗？

sentences.name: 句子56
sentences.correct: M: I would guess around 6:00 p.m.
sentences.translate: M： 我猜测大约在下午6点左右。

sentences.name: 句子57
sentences.correct: W: Do you have the time?
sentences.translate: W： 你有时间吗？

sentences.name: 句子58
sentences.translate: M： 现在是4:30。

sentences.name: 句子59
sentences.correct: W: Can you recommend any good restaurants downtown that offer meals at a reasonable price?
sentences.translate: W： 你能推荐市中心任何价格合理的好餐馆吗？

sentences.name: 句子60
sentences.correct: M: The Mexican restaurant, La Fajita, is fantastic.
sentences.translate: M： 墨西哥餐厅La Fajita非常棒。

sentences.name: 句子61
sentences.correct: It's not as inexpensive as other places I know, but the decoration is very authentic, and the portions are larger than most places I've been to.
sentences.translate: 它不像我所知道的其他地方那么便宜，但装饰非常真实，而且比我去过的大多数地方都要大。

sentences.name: 句子62
sentences.correct: W: Sounds great!
sentences.translate: W： 听起来不错！

sentences.name: 句子63
sentences.correct: How do I get there from the museum?
sentences.translate: 我从博物馆怎么去那里？

sentences.name: 句子64
sentences.correct: M: You can catch the subway right outside the museum.
sentences.translate: M： 你可以在博物馆外乘地铁。

sentences.name: 句子65
sentences.correct: There are buses that run that way, but you would have to transfer a couple of times.
sentences.translate: 有这样的公交车，但你必须换乘几次。

sentences.name: 句子66
sentences.correct: And there are taxis too, but they don't run by the museum that often.
sentences.translate: 也有出租车，但它们不经常经过博物馆。

sentences.name: 句子67
sentences.correct: W: Okay. Thanks.
sentences.translate: W： 好吧。谢谢。

sentences.name: 句子68
sentences.correct: Questions 8 to 11 are based on the conversation you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题8至11基于你刚才听到的对话。

sentences.name: 第 8 题 69
sentences.correct: 8. What can we learn about the driver?
sentences.translate: 8.我们能从司机身上学到什么？

sentences.name: 第 9 题 70
sentences.correct: 9. What can we learn about the museum?
sentences.translate: 9.我们可以从博物馆学到什么？

sentences.name: 第 10 题 71
sentences.correct: 10. What can we learn about the Mexican restaurant?
sentences.translate: 10.我们可以从墨西哥餐厅学到什么？

sentences.name: 第 11 题 72
sentences.correct: 11. What does the man say about the traffic near the museum?
sentences.translate: 11.那人说博物馆附近的交通怎么样？

sentences.name: 句子73
sentences.correct: Conversation Two M: Wait. What are you doing?
sentences.translate: 对话二M：等等。你在做什么？

sentences.name: 句子74
sentences.correct: W: What does it look like I'm doing?
sentences.translate: W： 我在做什么？

sentences.name: 句子75
sentences.correct: I'm having your car towed away for illegal parking. You parked your car in a no-parking area. Look, sir.
sentences.translate: 我要把你的车拖走，因为你违章停车。你把车停在禁止停车的区域。看，先生。

sentences.name: 句子76
sentences.correct: There's a sign right there that says, “Tow-away zone. No parking between the hours from 7 a.m. to 6 p.m.” M: What sign? Oh, that one?
sentences.translate: 那边有个标志，上面写着：“拖车区。早上7点到下午6点之间禁止停车。”m：什么标志？哦，那个？

sentences.name: 句子77
sentences.correct: Those tree branches are covering it.
sentences.translate: 那些树枝盖住了它。

sentences.name: 句子78
sentences.correct: W: Take that complaint up with the city.
sentences.translate: W： 向市政府投诉。

sentences.name: 句子79
sentences.correct: I'm just here to uphold the law.
sentences.translate: 我只是来维护法律的。

sentences.name: 句子80
sentences.correct: Anyway, you can clearly see it once you get out of your car.
sentences.translate: 不管怎样，一旦你下车，你就能清楚地看到它。

sentences.name: 句子81
sentences.correct: M: But my car was only here for five minutes.
sentences.translate: M： 但我的车只在这里呆了五分钟。

sentences.name: 句子82
sentences.correct: I just had to run into this building to drop off some clothing at the homeless shelter.
sentences.translate: 我只好跑进这栋楼，把一些衣服送到无家可归者收容所。

sentences.name: 句子83
sentences.correct: Just try to help people in need.
sentences.translate: 试着帮助有需要的人。

sentences.name: 句子84
sentences.correct: W: The homeless shelter is six blocks down the road.
sentences.translate: W： 无家可归者收容所就在路的六个街区外。

sentences.name: 句子85
sentences.correct: Anyway, here's your ticket, and the address where you can pick up your car is found on the back.
sentences.translate: 不管怎样，这是你的票，你可以在后面找到取车的地址。

sentences.name: 句子86
sentences.correct: M: What? One hundred and fifty dollars?
sentences.translate: M： 什么？一百五十美元？

sentences.name: 句子87
sentences.correct: That's, that's outrageous.
sentences.translate: 这太离谱了。

sentences.name: 句子88
sentences.correct: Completely ludicrous.
sentences.translate: 完全可笑。

sentences.name: 句子89
sentences.correct: W: Sorry, sir.
sentences.translate: W： 对不起，先生。

sentences.name: 句子90
sentences.correct: M: And you mean you're going to tow the car away?
sentences.translate: M： 你是说你要把车拖走？

sentences.name: 句子91
sentences.correct: I'm standing right here. Look.
sentences.translate: 我就站在这里。你看。

sentences.name: 句子92
sentences.correct: How about two tickets for a lecture on the history of English language tomorrow night at the library?
sentences.translate: 明晚在图书馆听英语史讲座的两张票怎么样？

sentences.name: 句子93
sentences.correct: W: Sir, it's illegal to bribe an officer.
sentences.translate: W： 先生，贿赂警察是违法的。

sentences.name: 句子94
sentences.correct: M: Wait a minute.
sentences.translate: M： 等一下。

sentences.name: 句子95
sentences.correct: Here are some coupons for a free burger at that restaurant across the street.
sentences.translate: 这是街对面那家餐厅免费汉堡的优惠券。

sentences.name: 句子96
sentences.correct: You can buy one and get the second one half price.
sentences.translate: 你可以买一个，然后半价。

sentences.name: 句子97
sentences.correct: W: Sorry, sir. Have a good day.
sentences.translate: W： 对不起，先生。祝您今天过得愉快。

sentences.name: 句子98
sentences.correct: Questions 12 to 15 are based on the conversation you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 问题12至15基于你刚才听到的对话。

sentences.name: 第 12 题 99
sentences.correct: 12. Why does the woman have the man's car towed away?
sentences.translate: 12.为什么女人要把男人的车拖走？

sentences.name: 第 13 题 100
sentences.correct: 13. Why does the man fail to see the sign?
sentences.translate: 13.为什么那人看不见标志？

sentences.name: 第 14 题 101
sentences.correct: 14. How does the woman react to the man's explanation?
sentences.translate: 14.女人对男人的解释有何反应？

sentences.name: 第 15 题 102
sentences.correct: 15. What will the woman most probably do?
sentences.translate: 15.这位女士最有可能做什么？

sentences.name: C 部分题干103
sentences.correct: Section C Directions: In this section, you will hear three passages.
sentences.translate: C节说明：在本节中，你将听到三段。

sentences.name: C 部分题干104
sentences.correct: At the end of each passage, you will hear three or four questions.
sentences.translate: 在每篇文章的末尾，你会听到三到四个问题。

sentences.name: C 部分题干105
sentences.correct: Both the passage and the questions will be spoken only once.
sentences.translate: 文章和问题都只讲一次。

sentences.name: C 部分题干106
sentences.correct: After you hear a question, you must choose the best answer from the four choices marked A), B), C) and D).
sentences.translate: 听到问题后，您必须从标记为a）、B）、C）和D）的四个选项中选择最佳答案。

sentences.name: C 部分题干结束107
sentences.correct: Then mark the corresponding letter on Answer Sheet 1 with a single line through the centre.
sentences.translate: 然后在答题纸1上用一条穿过中心的线标记相应的字母。

sentences.name: 句子108
sentences.correct: Passage One A new study proves the old Roman saying, “A sound mind in a sound body”— the more fit one's heart is, the more one's brain seems to benefit.
sentences.translate: 一项新的研究证明了古罗马谚语“健全的身体，健全的心灵”——一个人的心脏越健康，他的大脑似乎就越受益。

sentences.name: 句子109
sentences.correct: The scientists discovered that cardiovascular fitness was linked with overall intelligence, although the same did not hold true for muscle strength and brainpower.
sentences.translate: 科学家们发现，心血管健康与整体智力有关，尽管肌肉力量和脑力并非如此。

sentences.name: 句子110
sentences.correct: Cardiovascular fitness was also linked with scores on tests of logical, verbal, technical and visual capabilities and even socioeconomic status and educational attainment later in life.
sentences.translate: 心血管健康状况也与逻辑、语言、技术和视觉能力测试的分数有关，甚至与以后的社会经济地位和教育程度有关。

sentences.name: 句子111
sentences.correct: Cardiovascular exercise increases blood flow to the brain, supplying it with more oxygen and nutrients.
sentences.translate: 心血管运动增加了大脑的血流量，为大脑提供了更多的氧气和营养。

sentences.name: 句子112
sentences.correct: Moreover, during exercise, growth factors are produced that could improve brain structure over time.
sentences.translate: 此外，在运动过程中，会产生生长因子，随着时间的推移，这些生长因子可以改善大脑结构。

sentences.name: 句子113
sentences.correct: This not only includes more and stronger connections between nerve cells, but also more neurons and supporting cells.
sentences.translate: 这不仅包括神经细胞之间更多更强的连接，还包括更多的神经元和支持细胞。

sentences.name: 句子114
sentences.correct: From animal experiments we know this is the case especially in the hippocampus, a region of the brain that is important for learning and memory.
sentences.translate: 从动物实验中我们知道，尤其是在海马体，这是一个对学习和记忆很重要的大脑区域。

sentences.name: 句子115
sentences.correct: It is also possible that smarter people exercise more. However, the twin data suggests not.
sentences.translate: 聪明的人也可能锻炼得更多。然而，双胞胎数据表明并非如此。

sentences.name: 句子116
sentences.correct: When the researchers looked at twins, they found that the environment played the biggest role in these links.
sentences.translate: 当研究人员观察双胞胎时，他们发现环境在这些联系中起着最大的作用。

sentences.name: 句子117
sentences.correct: The fitter twin is also the more intelligent twin.
sentences.translate: 更健康的双胞胎也是更聪明的双胞胎。

sentences.name: 句子118
sentences.correct: Past research has suggested that cardiovascular fitness can benefit the minds of older adults.
sentences.translate: 过去的研究表明，心血管健康对老年人的大脑有益。

sentences.name: 句子119
sentences.correct: For instance, it can delay or reduce the onset and progression of dementia and Alzheimer's disease.
sentences.translate: 例如，它可以延缓或减少痴呆症和阿尔茨海默病的发作和进展。

sentences.name: 句子120
sentences.correct: The findings can be used to argue for a more balanced school curriculum.
sentences.translate: 这些发现可以用来为更平衡的学校课程辩护。

sentences.name: 句子121
sentences.correct: It is a better argument for school kids to grasp that they can be more successful in life if they study and exercise.
sentences.translate: 这是一个更好的论点，让学童们明白，如果他们学习和锻炼，他们可以在生活中取得更大的成功。

sentences.name: 句子122
sentences.correct: Questions 16 to 19 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答问题16至19。

sentences.name: 第 16 题 123
sentences.correct: 16. What does the new study find?
sentences.translate: 16.这项新研究发现了什么？

sentences.name: 第 17 题 124
sentences.correct: 17. How does cardiovascular exercise benefit our brain?
sentences.translate: 17.心血管运动对我们的大脑有什么好处？

sentences.name: 第 18 题 125
sentences.correct: 18. What do we learn about twins according to the researchers?
sentences.translate: 18.根据研究人员的说法，我们对双胞胎有什么了解？

sentences.name: 第 19 题 126
sentences.correct: 19. What enlightenment on education can be got from the study?
sentences.translate: 19.这项研究对教育有什么启示？

sentences.name: 句子127
sentences.correct: Passage Two With growing numbers of people living alone, either by choice or circumstance, friendships can occupy the emotional space that other people fill with spouses or significant others.
sentences.translate: 随着越来越多的人选择或因环境而独居，友谊可以占据其他人与配偶或重要他人之间的情感空间。

sentences.name: 句子128
sentences.correct: Friends can link us to broader social networks and help enrich our lives.
sentences.translate: 朋友可以将我们与更广泛的社交网络联系起来，帮助丰富我们的生活。

sentences.name: 句子129
sentences.correct: Friendships are what make us unique human.
sentences.translate: 友谊使我们成为独一无二的人。

sentences.name: 句子130
sentences.correct: There is no other species that interacts so widely with other members of their species.
sentences.translate: 没有其他物种与它们物种的其他成员如此广泛地相互作用。

sentences.name: 句子131
sentences.correct: Solid friendships provide needed validation that a person is valuable and of interest to other people.
sentences.translate: 牢固的友谊提供了所需的验证，即一个人是有价值的，并且对其他人感兴趣。

sentences.name: 句子132
sentences.correct: Relationships help people feel that they're worthy, that they are capable, that they can set goals and accomplish them, and that they can control their life.
sentences.translate: 人际关系帮助人们觉得自己有价值，有能力，可以设定目标并实现目标，可以控制自己的生活。

sentences.name: 句子133
sentences.correct: Friendships could be represented by three concentric circles as very close, close, and not-so-close but still meaningful personal ties.
sentences.translate: 友谊可以用三个同心圆来表示，即非常亲密、亲密和不那么亲密但仍然有意义的个人关系。

sentences.name: 句子134
sentences.correct: A person's inner circle usually includes close family members and friends who are thought of as family.
sentences.translate: 一个人的核心圈子通常包括亲密的家人和被视为家人的朋友。

sentences.name: 句子135
sentences.correct: Close friendships display strong support and affection.
sentences.translate: 亲密的友谊表现出强烈的支持和感情。

sentences.name: 句子136
sentences.correct: A close friend who listens and pays attention to you, is willing to help you, and has shared interests.
sentences.translate: 一个倾听并关注你、愿意帮助你、有共同兴趣的亲密朋友。

sentences.name: 句子137
sentences.correct: There is give-and-take and often a balance that doesn't put too much weight on one party.
sentences.translate: 双方相互让步，而且往往是一种平衡，不会给一方带来太大的压力。

sentences.name: 句子138
sentences.correct: Developing and maintaining friendships requires continuous attention.
sentences.translate: 发展和维持友谊需要持续的关注。

sentences.name: 句子139
sentences.correct: Give-and-take is important.
sentences.translate: 给予和接受很重要。

sentences.name: 句子140
sentences.correct: Other elements of solid friendships include paying attention to what's going on in a friend's life, seeking out some shared interests and participating in activities together, and being able to confide deeply to a friend.
sentences.translate: 牢固友谊的其他要素包括关注朋友生活中发生的事情，寻找一些共同的兴趣，一起参加活动，以及能够向朋友倾诉。

sentences.name: 句子141
sentences.correct: Questions 20 to 22 are based on the passage you have just heard.
sentences.translate: 根据你刚才听到的文章，回答20至22题。

sentences.name: 第 20 题 142
sentences.correct: 20. Why does the speaker say friendships are unique to human beings?
sentences.translate: 20.为什么演讲者说友谊是人类独有的？

sentences.name: 第 21 题 143
sentences.correct: 21. What can we learn about the friendship circles?

sentences.name: 句子145
sentences.correct: Passage Three The Exmobaby, a tiny shirt designed to monitor an infant's heartbeat, skin temperature and movement with updates sent to parents via the text message.
sentences.translate: Exmobaby是一件小衬衫，旨在监测婴儿的心跳、皮肤温度和运动，并通过短信向父母发送最新信息。

sentences.name: 句子146
sentences.correct: The technology is designed to give new parents peace of mind.
sentences.translate: 这项技术旨在让新手父母放心。

sentences.name: 句子147
sentences.correct: Baby is crying and you're not sure if she means “Feed me” or “I'm sleepy.” Exmobaby.com's “About” section says that its software records previous physical states and attaches a motivation, such as hunger or tiredness, which can allow the system to predict likely causes of future events.
sentences.translate: 宝宝在哭，你不确定她是指“喂我”还是“我困了”。Exmobaby.com的“关于”部分说，它的软件记录了以前的身体状态，并附加了一个动机，比如饥饿或疲劳，这可以让系统预测未来事件的可能原因。

sentences.name: 句子148
sentences.correct: Over time, the technology can supposedly help predict a baby's emotions and behavior.
sentences.translate: 随着时间的推移，这项技术可以帮助预测婴儿的情绪和行为。

sentences.name: 句子149
sentences.correct: The product is marketed specifically to first-time parents, who are “particularly apprehensive” about their new role and are overwhelmingly ridden with worry.
sentences.translate: 该产品专门针对首次为人父母的人进行营销，他们对自己的新角色“特别担心”，并且忧心忡忡。

sentences.name: 句子150
sentences.correct: The website cites an increase of premature births as a reason parents' concerns are at an all-time high and even goes so far as to claim that the technology can reduce the rate of infant deaths.
sentences.translate: 该网站指出，早产的增加是父母担忧达到历史最高水平的原因之一，甚至声称该技术可以降低婴儿死亡率。

sentences.name: 句子151
sentences.correct: But not everyone is convinced.
sentences.translate: 但并不是每个人都相信。

sentences.name: 句子152
sentences.correct: The antis hold that the Exmobaby is just another product targeted to vulnerable first-time parents who “spend too much money on baby crap.” If you do want a piece of the Exmobaby action, you'll have to wait.
sentences.translate: 反对者认为，Exmobaby只是针对“在婴儿垃圾上花太多钱”的弱势首次父母的另一种产品。

sentences.name: 句子153
sentences.correct: It's only in investigational stages and can't be purchased yet.
sentences.translate: 它还处于研究阶段，还不能购买。
